title: best fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt together the butter and marshmallows. In large saucepan, cook the milk and sugar.
Boil hard for 8 minutes, then fold the marshmallows carefully and add the chocolate chips.
Stir until melted and quickly add the nuts and beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan and mark in squares. Cool and cut.

title: mom's chop suey
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add celery and onions.
Cover with water. Simmer until tender.
Thicken juice from sprouts and vegetables with cornstarch mixed with the juice.
Add soy sauce, brown sugar and vinegar.
Add sprouts and vegetables and meat.
Heat through and pour over rice or noodles.
Amounts can be varied to individual tastes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Heat butter/margarine in large skillet.
Brown crushed garlic until golden, then discard.
Saute chicken until browned on all sides.
Add sliced mushrooms and Marsala; cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Put ham in chunks in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer potatoes on top.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes. Grate cheese and top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco mix and 1 cup water. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
When ready to serve, combine lettuce, peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese, taco chips and cooled meat mixture.
Toss together with dressing.
Serve immediately.

title: herbed pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops.
Mix well.
Place chops in shallow dish.
Pour marinade over chops.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning meat occasionally.
Remove pork chops from marinade and place on rack of broiling pan.
Broil 10 to 12 minutes on each side or until done, turning and basting once with marinade.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Combine water, sugar and vinegar in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil. Cover.
Cook 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook mixture to soft ball stage.

title: hot squash casserole(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: To prepare:
Cook squash, green pepper and onion until tender. Drain and mash.
Add cheese and tomatoes.
Place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle broken tortilla chips on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: carol's beef stew
directions: Brown stew beef in large pot (no fat or oil, no flour).
When meat is brown, add water to cover, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and onion; simmer until meat is nice and tender (several hours).
Add potatoes, carrots and any other veggies; cook until done.
Mix cornstarch and water; put into stew to thicken, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Melt and bring to a boil. Stir for one minute while boiling. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Beat until right consistency to spread (about 30 minutes).

title: bacon, mushroom cheeseburger
directions: First fry bacon on stove.
Fire the grill up.
Cook hamburger on grill (after pattied up).
Five minutes before hamburger is done, warm mushroom gravy up on stove.
When hamburgers are done, lay slices of cheese on them, then lay 2 to 3 half slices of bacon on them.
Spoon on mushroom gravy on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8 people.

title: toffee bars
directions: Blend brown sugar and butter, bring to boil exactly 2 mins. Remove from heat and add pecans.
Spread over crackers and bake. Bake 10 min. at 350 degrees, cool slightly and cut.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in blender, then add oil and vinegar alternately and very slowly until all ingredients are blended. Good on fruit salads.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1/3 cup milk, melted margarine and nuts.
Melt 1/2 cup milk and the caramels.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place half of the cake mixture in pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate for 12 hours. Mix every once in a while.
(Pickles will keep in refrigerator for about 1 month.)

title: cheese corn bake
directions: Melt butter.
Add to softened cheese and stir.
Add other ingredients and stir to mix.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: mama's squash bake
directions: Wash all squash and scrub clean.
Dice yellow squash and zucchini; boil in salted water until barley tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: hot and sour ketchup
directions: Grind all of this and mix together.
Add canning salt to taste. Place in jars not too tight.
I use two piece lids; it won't seal but it will keep.
Store in dark place.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 or 10-inch pie pan (oleo or butter may be used to grease pan).

title: corn flake muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
Measure corn flakes and milk into large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine.
Let stand about 2 minutes, or until softened.
Add oil and egg; beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Grease pans with 12 muffin cups.
Pour batter evenly into them.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed puffs
directions: In
medium
saucepan,
combine	water, butter and salt. Slowly bring
to boiling, stirring occasionally.	Remove from heat; beat in
flour.
Return
to
low heat; continue beating until mixture forms a
ball
and	leaves	side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs,
one at a time, beating until mixture is shiny.
Drop by teaspoonfuls
two inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in	400°
oven
about
20 minutes or until puffs are golden brown. Cool
on
wire
rack.
Makes
to 7 dozen puffs.
(The puffs can be frozen and taken from freezer an hour before
serving. Fill
puffs
just
before serving to avoid soggy puffs.) Good.

title: cheesecake
directions: Make cracker crust by breaking up the crackers into crumbs in a bowl and stirring in the melted butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve the jello in the 1 cup of boiling water and add the lemon juice, allow it to jell but not to set, set aside.
Beat together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth, add the evaporated milk and beat until really thick.
Then add the jello mixture to the milk and cheese mixture.
Pour into cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Parboil peppers 5 minutes; drain.
Cut peppers in half; remove seeds and stems and rinse.
Place in baking dish.
Combine coarse bread crumbs with milk.
Saute onion in margarine (or chopped parsley).
Combine onions with meat substitute, sauce, salt, pepper and herb and/or buttered bread crumbs.
Stuff peppers with mixture and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on grill over medium-hot coals or rack of broiler.
Brush with 1/2 of salad dressing mixture.
Grill or broil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn. Brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue grilling or broiling for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shells. Cook at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: cherry vanilla "ice cream"
directions: In a bowl or blender container process vanilla dietary frozen dessert until smooth.
Transfer to a 1-quart freezer-safe bowl and add fresh or frozen cherries (no sugar added) cut into halves and vanilla extract.
Stir to combine.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until hardened.
When ready to serve, scoop into serving bowls.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: sausage peloriff
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and hot pepper in butter.
Put sausage in sauteed mixture and cook slightly.
Put mixture in rice cooker with rice, water and beef broth cubes.
Set to cook as indicated on rice cooker for 1 1/2 cups rice.

title: spinach cottage cheese salad(a green and white treat for a crowd)
directions: Clean spinach and tear out stems.
Mix with lettuce torn in bite-size pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp, crumble and add to greens.
Mix sugar, onion, oil, vinegar, salt and mustard.
Beat well.
Add half of dressing to greens and the rest to the cottage cheese.
Chill.
Add cheese mixture just before serving.
Serves 12.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: In sauce pan bring liquids to a boil.
Whisk in gelatin, pudding mixes.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Fold in oranges, pineapple, cool whip.

title: mock lasagne
directions: Brown sausage; drain off fat. Add salt, pepper, garlic and basil. Add 1/2 cup water. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 each starting with macaroni, Ricotta cheese, shredded cheese, then meat sauce; repeat.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: sunny lemon squares
directions: Sift flour once; add confectioners sugar, salt and cut in butter.
Should resemble coarse meal.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: nut-filled wreaths
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream again.
Beat in egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour gradually to make soft dough. Remove 1/3 cup dough.
Mix in pecans, corn syrup and almond; set aside.

title: sally's salad
directions: Mix hot water, jellos, cold water, apples, and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate until set.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, cornstarch, and salt.
Boil until thick and then cool.
Once cool, add lemon juice and cool whip.
Top jello with this mixture and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put strawberries in cooked pie shell.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and water; cook over medium heat until clear.
Add jello.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together; churn according to instructions.

title: peanut butter chocolate rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows on low in large nonstick pan until marshmallows are melted. Stir in peanut butter. Quickly add Rice Krispies and chocolate chips. Stir well with large wooden spatula. Pour into 9 x 13 pan that has been greased with butter or margarine.

title: helen's chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Pour in double boiler; bring to boil and stir until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell and let cool thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies (3 at a time) in blender or food processor. Divide into 3 parts.
Cream together the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix milk and pudding.
Add whipped cream; combine the 2 mixes.
Layer 1/3 of the cookies, half of the mixture, 1/3 cookies, other half of mixture and sprinkle other 1/3 cookies on top.
Use a new 8-inch plastic flowerpot. Refrigerate overnight.

title: president reagan's favorite macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in salt water until tender; drain.
Stir in beaten egg and butter.
Mix dry mustard and a little salt and pepper in a tablespoon of hot water.
Add milk.
Add cheese, leaving a little to sprinkle on top.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Add milk.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until custard is set and top is crusty at 350° (45 minutes).

title: hot beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Microwave until hot.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: three stew
directions: Mix ingredients together (unbrowned) in ovenproof casserole. Bake in oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Can be done in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low.
Serve with broad egg noodles.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and check beans.
Soak overnight in water; drain.
In 8 to 10-quart stock pot, put beans.
Add water, smoked ham or ham bone, parsley, chicken bouillon cubes, thyme and bay leaf.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 hours.
Add chicken breast, celery, carrots, chopped tomatoes, onions and garlic. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add kielbasa or smoked sausage and white wine.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 5 quarts.
Refrigerate when cool for at least 12 hours (24 is better).
Remove bone, bay leaf and fat before reheating.

title: charleston shrimp creole
directions: In a large cast-iron skillet, heat until smoking, combine bacon drippings and all veggies; cook until medium tender.
Add 1 cup water.
Combine shrimp and cook, covered, until meat has turned white.
Remove from heat; pour mixture over rice, then stand back because everyone will run over you trying to get the first portion.
Serves 6.

title: sweet uncooked cucumber pickles
directions: Soak for 14 days in brine water the whole cucumbers, then slice.
Soak for 6 hours in vinegar; drain.
Pour the spice and sugar in over cucumbers and let stand.
The sugar will make plenty of syrup to cover pickles.
This pickle may be stored in stone jar until used.
Sealing is not necessary.
This is all cold.
The pickles are never to be heated.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Serve on lettuce.

title: divinity
directions: Cook 1 cup of sugar and water to 242° on candy thermometer. Pour slowly over egg whites.
Cook 3 cups of sugar, corn syrup, hot water, salt and cream of tartar to 252° on candy thermometer. Pour slowly over egg white mixture, beating well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: taco dip #1
directions: Evenly spread cream cheese on the 10 to 12-inch round plate.
Cover with taco sauce.
Next, sprinkle taco cheese, followed by shredded lettuce and top with tomato.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Serve with taco chips. Great for parties.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Cut tortillas in strips (1 to 2 inches).
Mix cream of chicken soup with whipping cream and stir.
Dice onions, brown and have them ready.
Grate cheese.
Layer in a large square dish.

title: homemade brown sugar syrup
directions: Mix brown sugar and water in saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat and simmer about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add maple flavoring. Use hot or cold over pancakes, waffles, ice cream, French toast or rice pudding.

title: orange-pumpkin cake squares
directions: Cream the shortening.
Gradually add the sugar, beating well. Add pumpkin, eggs and orange juice; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Stir into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth (about 10 minutes). Put in graham cracker pie shell.
Put cherry pie filling on top.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and seasoning with mixer on medium until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and peppers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with bread sticks.
Makes 10 servings.
Preparation time: 5 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain juices into large saucepan.
Add brown sugar; heat until boiling.
Lower heat; add curry powder and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat; add fruit.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry pork chops
directions: In a bowl, combine 1 cup of whole berries, bread crumbs, water, melted butter, celery, onion, green pepper and seasonings. Stuff pork chop pockets with mixture and close with toothpicks. In a large skillet, heat the tablespoon of cooking oil and brown chops on both sides.
Remove chops from skillet and place in baking dish.
In a small saucepan,
mash the remaining strawberries and combine with brown sugar and soy sauce; baste chops.
Reserve the rest for basting chops.
Cover baking dish with foil and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 90 minutes. Remove chops at 30-minute intervals to taste.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in large pieces and cook until tender. Drain well.
Melt margarine in pan and saute chopped onion.
Add to potatoes.
Add parsley, onion salt and garlic salt to taste and toss potatoes gently.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Slice Velveeta cheese paper thin and place on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in bananas.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to mixture. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350° (or until done).

title: salsa
directions: Place tomatoes in blender.
Cover and run on lowest speed for 2 seconds to chop tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes with onion, cilantro, lemon juice, garlic and pepper sauce.
Add additional pepper sauce if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.
tags: Del Monte Italian style stewed tomatoes

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Stir together the baking powder and salt.
Cut shortening into flour with a pastry blender, then stir in milk with a fork.
Knead by folding, pressing and turning about 10 times on a lightly floured board.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread with soft butter; sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough along long side.
Pinch long edge to seal.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place, cut side down, in greased muffin pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli 2 minutes less than package directions.
Drain and place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix the cornstarch with a small amount of chicken broth in a saucepan at medium heat. Gradually add the remaining broth.
Cook about 5 minutes more. Stir in the milk and cheese.
Pour half the mixture over the broccoli.
Then layer the chicken slices over the sauce.
Pour the remaining sauce over the chicken slices.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quiche
directions: Roll out pie crust to 12-inch round on slightly floured board. Fit into dish, trim edges, pricking all over with fork.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 5 minutes; remove to wire rack and cool.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in plastic bag.
Blend with melted butter. Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cookie mixture.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and 10x sugar in mixer.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Combine puddings and milk; mix in mixer until thick. Pour pudding mixture on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Oreo cookie crumbs on top of Cool Whip.
Chill to set.

title: eloise's cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolk, flour and salt.
Spread over 2 ungreased cookie sheets (will be spread very thin).
Brush egg white on top of dough.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: spice in a shaker
directions: Blend together and put in shaker.
Pass up the salt.
Just as good as Mrs. Dash.

title: fast baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Brush each half with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and cheese.
Place cut side down on oil cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potato is fork-tender.

title: "sugar cookies"
directions: Cream sugars and butter or margarine.
Add eggs; stir in oil and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Blend well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Use small glass dipped in white sugar to press balls flat.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into a bowl. Add the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Stir in the oats, and chocolate chips, nuts, raisins or coconut.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Heat milk just until hot.
Add sugar, salt and shortening. Cool.
Soften yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
Add to milk mixture the yeast, soda and half of flour.
Beat well.
Add rest of flour.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash apples and take out the core.
Do not peel.
Put apples in baking dish.
Mix honey, water and lemon rind.
Pour over apples.
Cover the dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour pan juices over the apples every 15 minutes.
Take off the cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Take out of oven and cool.

title: superb and simple meat loaf
directions: Mix well and place in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Combine brown
sugar,
salt and milk in saucepan; bring to boil. Cook slowly
for
minutes
or until slightly thickened. Remove from pan.
Add margarine
and vanilla and cool.
Then add powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Press into greased pan and cool.

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Mix together cheeses, eggs, sugar and parsley.
Stuff mixture into shells.
Spread sauce on bottom of 2 cake pans.
Place stuffed shells in.
Cover with sauce.
Cover tightly with tinfoil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients once. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, beaten lightly, then dry ingredients and milk. Add oatmeal and raisins. Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until lightly brown. Makes 4 dozen+, depending on size. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: cranberry lime rickey
directions: Put cranberry juice cocktail and sugar in a blender.
Blend for a few seconds on high speed until the sugar is dissolved. Pour into a large glass with ice.
Squeeze the lime wedge and add to glass. Top with lemon-lime soda.
Garnish with a lime wedge. Makes 1 serving.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions in 9-inch glass dish.
Beat together the remaining ingredients and pour over bacon mix. Microwave on 50% power for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix sour cream with milk; add 1 1/2 cans chili pepper.
Add rice and cheese to mixture.
Put in a greased pan.
Top with 1/2 can chili pepper and 5 ounces grated sharp cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy muffin bites
directions: Mix shrimp, margarine, cheese spread, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Spread mixture onto English muffin halves.
Cut into quarters.
Broil 2 to 4 minutes or until cheese bubbles or microwave 15 to 30 seconds or until cheese bubbles.

title: potato puff
directions: Mash potatoes with butter and milk; mix in cream cheese.
Beat in egg, pimiento and onion.
Turn mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish or casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fireplace hot chocolate
directions: Put all ingredients in blender except milk.
Heat milk on stove or in microwave; heat on high for 5 minutes.
Pour 1 cup at a time into blender, beating on high.
Pour into mugs; garnish with marshmallows, cinnamon stick or peppermint stick.
Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet chocolate pies
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar.
Set it aside.
Mix eggs and milk together and set aside.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add sugar mixture.
Stir and then add milk and egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring continuously.
Pour in cooked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip or meringue.
This recipe will make one deep dish or two regular pies.

title: blitz torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla. Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Spread in two layer pans (greased).
Cover with meringue or egg whites and 1 cup sugar.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine chicken breasts, onion, garlic and butter in 2 1/2 quart microwave-safe dish.
Cover and cook on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Blend cornstarch with broth and add with remaining ingredients to chicken mixture.
Cover and cook 7 minutes or until thickened.
Stir twice.
Fluff with fork.

title: mock quiche
directions: Line sides of pie plate with cheese slices. Beat eggs; add milk, onions and spinach. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese. Pour egg mix over cheese slices. Add rest of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Let cool 5 minutes; slice and serve.

title: hamburger pot pie onion pastry(double crust)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
For metal pie plate, 425°.
Mix flour and Crisco until mixture is uniform.
Mix onion, salt and water. Sprinkle on water a tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Work dough into a firm ball with hands.
Divide in half and form 2 flat circles.
On a floured surface, roll out bottom crust, until 1 1/2-inches larger than a 9-inch pie plate.
Place crust in pie plate, time even with edge.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Cook beef and onions until brown. Drain.
Stir in seasoning.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.

title: baked pita chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut each pita bread in half horizontally. Cut each half into 8 triangles. Arrange in single layer on flat baking stone. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Repeat until all chips are baked. Cool on cooling rack. Yield 112 chips (16 servings). Seven chips 50 calories.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Step 1:
Pour milk in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire beater until well blended.

title: zesty sausage squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick with milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Spread in well-greased pan (or spray with Pam) casserole (8 1/2-inch square pan).

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and let set until sugar dissolves.
Combine all ingredients together and serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in an oiled pan in 350° to 375° oven.
Make a Medium White Sauce; add 1 can peas and pour over salmon loaf to serve.

title: christina's favorite cookies(oatmeal)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies, 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing.

title: cobblestone bread
directions: Combine shortening, 1/3 cup sugar, salt and boiling water. Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour and egg.
Mix well and add to shortening mixture.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Blend remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Dip balls into sugar mixture.
Layer in rows in tube pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 475° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry salad frozen
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve frozen blocks. Always keep in freezer.

title: spinach yum yum!
directions: Cook spinach with salt and drain well.
Mix softened margarine and cheese and spread over spinach.
Sprinkle onions on top and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: rum punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 1 minute and cool.
Add juices, extract and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Use large can of pineapple and oranges; drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Add a little sugar.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Layer in dish in fine pieces.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers.
Put on top.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour vegies
directions: Sauce together the onion, green pepper, ginger, garlic powder, salt, cayenne pepper and chili powder in the vegetable oil until vegies are soft.
Add tomatoes, pineapple juice and tomato paste. Boil moderately, then reduce to simmer.
Add crushed pineapple, honey and vinegar.
Simmer.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In a large bowl or pot, mash potatoes with mixer or by hand until lumps are removed.
Add cream cheese in small pieces and butter.
Beat well until cheese and butter are melted.
Mix in the sour cream.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool for 20 minutes.
Mix last 3 ingredients and spread on top of pie.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: picnic bean bake
directions: Cook ground beef until browned.
Drain.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Mix beef and bacon and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or cook all day on low in crock-pot.

title: lemon sponge
directions: Mix flour and sugar with creamed butter.
Separate eggs and add yolks, milk, lemon juice and grated rind.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into the mixture and pour into individual custard cups or shallow baking dish.
Place in a pan of water.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve at room temperature or cold, plain or with whipped cream.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Mix Cool Whip, oleo, powdered sugar and pudding.
Cut each cake the long way 4 times.
Place 1/2 of the pieces in 9 x 13-inch.
Spread 1/2 Cool Whip mixture over cake.
Sprinkle 1/2 candy bars and nuts over this.
Repeat cake, Cool Whip and Butterfinger/nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple. Bring juice to a boil.
Pour over jello.
Mix well.
Let cool and add to other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except marshmallows.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Add marshmallows and brown.

title: mother's lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Put into refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Beat with a mixer until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients. Mold or put in Pyrex dish.
Must be made the day before serving.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to moderate 375°.
Pour cherry pie filling into 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine pancake mix, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Stir in egg until all ingredients are moistened.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water.
Combine next 4 ingredients; stir into bouillon mix.
Brown chicken in oil; add bouillon mixture, cooking until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts and rice.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup nuts.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Serves 4.

title: taco sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer slowly for about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally so it won't stick to the bottom.
Cook until reduced to nearly half.
Put in hot sterile jars with lids. Turn jars upside down; let sit until jars are cold.
Makes about 6 pints.
It too hot, use less peppers.

title: heavenly easy pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Let set, in refrigerator, at least 3 hours before eating.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Cut onions into very thin slices.
Saute in butter until transparent.
Beat eggs slightly, add evaporated milk and Worcestershire sauce and set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain, crumble and set aside.
Put sauteed onoins in pie shell. Sprinkle cheese over onions then pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at preheated 400° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: western round steak
directions: Trim fat off steak, pound meat and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip meat into egg, then cornflakes mixed with chili powder.
Brown meat on both sides in Wesson oil at medium heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: You will also need toothpicks and a disposable foil pan.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased square 9 x 9-inch pan, stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan evenly.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut cake top with ice cream and sauce from under cake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla. Add the eggs.
Mix well.
Mix in the peanut butter.
Add flour, a cup at a time to insure it is mixed thoroughly.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and crisscross with a fork.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk. Cook in a double boiler until thickened.
Beat yolks and add remaining milk.
Add egg mixture slowly to custard and cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook
potatoes in skin.
Cool, peel and shred on coarse grater or potatoes may be cubed.
Combine cheese and 4 tablespoons margarine
in saucepan.
Heat and stir until cheese is almost melted.
Remove
from
heat
and
blend in sour cream, onions, salt
and
pepper.
Fold
in
potatoes and spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Dot
with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cover and bake at 300°.

title: slush punch
directions: Freeze overnight.
Take out 2 hours ahead and beat occasionally.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until dissolved; cool.
Add fruit juices and bananas.
Blend well and freeze.
Let thaw about 2 hours before serving.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale in punch bowl and stir until slushy.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Gradually add macaroni and salt to rapidly boiling water so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain in colander; rinse with cold water and drain again.
While macaroni cooks, combine remaining ingredients except salad dressing in large bowl.
Break tuna into small pieces with fork.
Stir macaroni into tuna mixture.
Add salad dressing and chill.

title: tomato soup cake(old family recipe)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Combine other ingredients and add to mix.
Bake in greased angel food cake pan until toothpick comes out clean (approximately 30 minutes) at 350°.

title: mabel's escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350° with foil on top.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, jelly, butter, orange juice and spices. Mix well.
Roll fruit, nuts and raisins in flour and add to egg mixture; mix well with hands.
Put in pans and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.
Use a toothpick to test for doneness.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all the above ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the corn flakes, mixed with the oleo.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Break tamales.
Layer ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Pour tamale juice over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seventeen's fabulous fudge
directions: Stir to blend slightly the evaporated milk, sugar, marshmallows, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat in heavy pan, stirring constantly.
Continue to stir and boil five minutes.
(Mixture will brown slightly.) Remove from heat.

title: sesame steamed broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a baking sheet with foil. Spread sesame seeds in a thin layer. Bake, stirring occasionally, until golden, about 10 minutes.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Pat out rolls on a baking sheet, pinching together.
Bake 8 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Mix 2 (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, Ranch dressing and Miracle Whip.
Spread on cooled baked dough.
Cut up tomatoes, broccoli, peppers, celery, carrots and layer on top of the dough.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef and add the taco seasoning mix to it and simmer for 10 minutes.
Chop up the tomatoes and lettuce.
In a big bowl, combine all ingredients and toss.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, a little at a time, until batter is still.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan; bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from pan after about 30 minutes.

title: banana split magic muffins
directions: Mix together the softened ice cream and flour until the flour has disappeared.
Add strawberry and banana pieces and stir five times.
The batter will turn pink.
Fill pregreased muffin tins with batter.
Place chocolate chips on top of each muffin.
Place in oven and bake at 375° until done and slightly brown on top. Let cool for 15 minutes before removing from tins.

title: chili
directions: Put hamburger in pan.
Let brown.
Pour grease off.
Put back on stove.
Put ketchup and chili powder in.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add a little water if dry.

title: vegetable linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to directions; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain again.
Cut vegetables (onion, celery, yellow squash, zucchini and red bell pepper) in small cubes.
Combine vegetables with seasoning.

title: carrot-pineapple muffins
directions: Mix together flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and seasonings.
In a separate bowl, mix oil, egg, milk, carrots and pineapple with juice.
Pour into flour mixture; combine until ingredients are just moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans that have been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: biscuit roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar.
Add salt, oil and flour.
Knead a little.
Make into rolls and place in a greased pan.
(Grease top of rolls slightly.)
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes. Cook at 450°.
Make these as you start your meal and you can have them with the meal.

title: nellie's calico beans
directions: Fry ground meat, bacon and onion together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture and stir.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix together grated cheese, sausage and Bisquick. Knead until well mixed. Stuff jalapenos with jalapeno cheese. Roll out dough and cover each jalapeno. Deep-fry until golden brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash broccoli, onions and cauliflower.
Cut the vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp and then crumble it.
Mix together the Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Put the vegetables, bacon and cheese in a large bowl and add the dressing.
Chill for three hours and serve.

title: pecan chews
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Yield:
15 servings.

title: surprise chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Boil oil, margarine, water and cocoa. Pour into the flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Will burn easily.)

title: chow chow
directions: Bring to a boil the last 5 ingredients.
Add vegetables and put in jars.
Process for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Roll out bread dough on a floured surface.
Defrost broccoli and chop.
Lay Provolone cheese on dough.
Next add pepperoni, broccoli, ham, Colby cheese and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bring sides and ends of pastry up to the top and pinch to seal.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients on top of stove until thick.
Take off fire and add jello.
Let set until cool.
Cut strawberries into baked pie crust.
Pour cooked ingredients over top.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse, peel, dry and remove stems from mushrooms. Chop enough stems to make 1/2 cup and reserve for later.
Combine cream cheese, deviled ham, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup stem pieces, onion powder and pepper.
Fill caps.
Melt butter. Drizzle over them and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: popovers
directions: Sift flour and salt together and gradually add milk, beating with a wooden spoon to make a smooth batter.
Beat eggs until light and add to batter.
Add the melted butter and beat vigorously. Preheat oven to 450°.
Butter 9 holes of a muffin pan or an equal number of custard cups.
Let muffin pan or custard cups heat in the oven for 5 minutes.
Then fill 2/3 full with batter and bake for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook the carrots until tender and drain well.
Mix together: soup, sugar, oil, peppers and onion.
Pour over carrots and let set overnight.
Put casserole dish in a 350° oven and cook for 45 minutes.
Very good.

title: venison spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown venison; drain, add garlic salt and chopped onions. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add Manwich, tomato paste and water. Simmer 20 minutes longer.
Additional water may be added for thinner sauce.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Process all at high speed until ice is of snow consistency.

title: orange bread
directions: Boil gently until reduced to one cup in bulk.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients as written in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly and hot.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll stew meat pieces in flour.
Brown in heavy skillet or Dutch oven in butter and Crisco.
Add seasonings, onion, broth, mushrooms, potatoes, carrots, turnips and celery which has been cut into chunks.
Stir, then add water if necessary.
Cover and simmer for at least one hour or until done.

title: refrigerated cherry dessert
directions: Mix for crust:
Graham crackers, melted margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven
Oil
a
9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sift flour,
baking
powder, salt and baking soda into a mixing bowl and set aside.
Put egg, oil, orange juice, rind and sugar into blender container.
Cover
and
process at mix speed until rind is finely grated.
Stop blender and add into flour mixture and
mix by hand only
until
flour
is
moistened.
Pour
into prepared pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until cake is done.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add water, tomatoes, onions and bell pepper. Cook 10 minutes. Add rice, potatoes and chili powder. Simmer about 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bring milk and margarine to a boil.
Beat eggs and set aside. Mix sugar, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon.
Pour into milk mixture. Stir beaten eggs and vanilla into milk mixture also.
Put bread into baking dish and pour the mixture over the bread.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger in medium saucepan; drain fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together.
Put into 6 buttered individual casserole dishes.
Cover each portion with cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: kris kringle wreaths
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg, vanilla and almond extracts. Add sifted flour and salt.
Mix into dough.
Fill cookie press. Press out on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Beat for 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour in tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and oranges; mix well.
Add pecans.
Chill.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix and heat soups, milk and oleo.
Put rice in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour half of mixture over rice and mix.
Place chicken breasts on top and pour rest of soup mixture over all.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter, sugar and flavorings in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add flour and salt; mix well. Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
While warm, cut into bars and cool in pan.
Store in airtight tin.
Freeze well.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan with margarine.
Dump in pineapple and juice.
Spread in pan.
Dump in cherry pie filling.
Spread over pineapple but do not stir together.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit without stirring.
Slice margarine over all.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole, except 1 tablespoon of butter and 1/4 cup cracker crumbs, which are sprinkled on top of corn mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cups
directions: Note:
Need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups (clear).

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix the margarine with the Stove Top stuffing and its seasoning; set aside.
Mash the cooked squash and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix half the crumbs in the casserole, then put the rest of the crumbs on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a covered casserole dish that has been buttered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ranch party mix
directions: You will need 2 paper grocery bags.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Whip up salsa and cheese in bowl. Add cayenne red pepper for taste.
Chop up extra onion very fine, if needed.
Put tortillas in wax paper in microwave for 30 to 40 seconds to warm. Spread cheese mixture thin and not to edge.
Roll tortillas up real tight and slice. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash; add onion, sour cream, soup, salt and pepper. Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle layer of crumbs on bottom.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs and generous dots of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: baked custard without sugar
directions: Mix milk with hot water and pour over eggs, adding salt and nutmeg.
Pour into well buttered custard cups and top with a bit more nutmeg.
Place custard cups in a pan of hot water.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soften crumbs in milk; saute onions in 1/2 butter.
Add to crumbs.
Add beef, seasonings and egg.
Form into 1-inch balls. Saute in remaining butter for 10 minutes.
Add consomme, simmer covered for 5 minutes.
Remove meat to serving dish.
Blend flour and water and thicken liquid.
Pour over meat and serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press rolls out on 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet (ungreased). Bake as directed on package.
Mix cream cheese and dressings well and spread on baked crust.
Top with shredded cheese and vegetables.
Yield:
2 (10 x 15-inch) pizzas.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup milk, 3/4 cup melted butter or oleo. Press 1/2 of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Melt caramels with remaining 1/3 cup milk.
After 6 minutes, pour chocolate chips over cake. Sprinkle nuts over chocolate chips.
Cover with melted caramel. Crumble remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: yummy in the tummy slush
directions: Boil the water and sugar together; cool.
Pour 4 cups boiling water over the tea bags.
Cool.
Add the remaining ingredients. To serve, put 1/2 cup slush in glass and add 50/50 or sour mix to fill glass.

title: hamburger potato soup
directions: Fry hamburger, stirring fine with a spoon.
Add salt and pepper. Cut onion fine and fry with hamburger. Add flour and brown as for gravy. Dice and cook potatoes. Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Add this to fried hamburger. Stir and let boil a few seconds.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown 2 pounds ground beef.
Add 1 cup onions and continue browning.
Add large can tomato sauce and 1 package spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: mama's old fashioned blackberry dumplings
directions: Thaw berries on low heat.
Add sugar, then cook on medium for 20 minutes.
(Adjust amount of sugar to taste at this point.)
Add almond and nut oil.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple.
Let stand overnight.
Add strawberry jello.
Heat to boiling, boil 10 minutes and seal in jars.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix eggs, salt and milk together, then add flour (enough to make stiff dough).	Roll out; let stand (dry) for 30 minutes. Slice into strips and let dry for 2 hours.	Drop into boiling water or soup; cook uncovered for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vanilla chip orange brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix crumbs, cocoa and rind.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water and chips until well blended; spread evenly into greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Store tightly covered. Makes 20 to 24 brownies.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, water, oil and eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place drained peaches on top.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spoon on top of peaches. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: french market soup
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight or several hours.
Cook beans in water with ham, onion and garlic, about 3 hours.
Do not boil hard.
Remove ham bones.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 60 minutes.
Add more water, if necessary.
Stir frequently.
Serves many.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Beat together zucchini, sugar, egg, oil and grated lemon rind and add to sifted ingredients.
Stir in chopped nuts only until blended.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pacific punch
directions: Mix and serve with or without ice.
Garnish with cherry.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Combine yeast cakes in water.
Stir to dissolve.
Place shortening, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Add hot milk and stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm, then add dissolved yeast. Stir in eggs.
Gradually mix in flour and beat until batter is smooth.
Add flour until dough does not cling to bowl.
Place in a greased bowl.
Chill 2 to 24 hours in refrigerator.
Make into rolls and let rise until doubled.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream together brown sugar (3/4 cup if using commercial jam), eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Stir soda into buttermilk and jam. Add to sugar mixture.
Mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and ginger; add to mixture.
Mix well and pour into 2 well-greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° until they spring back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out and cool.
Put together and ice sides and top with Caramel Icing.

title: raspberry-applesauce salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and let set.
Mix together at room temperature cream cheese, sour cream, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and leave at room temperature, creaming occasionally, until marshmallows are melted.
Shortly before serving, spread cream mixture on Jell-O and sprinkle with nuts.

title: trash
directions: Melt chocolate (microwave directions on package) and pour over mix.
Stir to coat and spread to dry on wax paper.

title: hot onion dip
directions: Mix and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Serve with tart apple wedges (Granny Smith) and small bagel chips. Cut apples in half; remove core, then slice into 1/8th slices with skin on.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Simmer about 45 minutes to one hour.
Put in jars and seal hot.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into fritters.
Fry in deep fat and roll in powdered sugar, if desired.

title: brown rice
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Melt butter in a pan and add rice.
Stir until light brown and then add soup, water mixture, garlic and cheese.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old-timey hot cocoa drink
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Blend in hot water, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk. Stir and heat.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater until foamy.
Makes 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Put raw rice in bottom of 9-inch casserole.
Add cream of mushroom and celery soups and sherry diluted with water.
Add diced celery and sliced mushrooms; mix.
Skin and split chicken breasts, cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit bell ringer candies
directions: In processor, grind fruits and nuts.
Mix all ingredients together and shape mixture into balls.
The balls may then be dipped in melted chocolate and rolled in coconut or chopped nuts. Chill and keep in covered container.
A delicious candy that is not as sweet as other types.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add alternately with milk; blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Very good.

title: cocoa silk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, sift flour, cocoa powder, cream of tartar, baking soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine applesauce, honey, egg whites and vanilla. Gently stir into flour mixture and mix until just blended.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Puree undrained tomatoes in blender.
Put the tomatoes in a large pot.
Add tomato paste and 1 1/2 cups water, parsley, basil, salt, sugar, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered and stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.

title: baked cup custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla until blended, about 1 minute.
Add slowly while beating scalded milk.
Beat only until blended. Pour into custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Set cups in pan of hot water.
Bake in preheated oven (325°) about 45 minutes or until a silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop the first 6 ingredients coarsely and run through the blender until finely chopped.
Do not blend until smooth, leave little pieces.
Add the last 4 ingredients and blend again.
Serve very cold, topped with croutons, if desired.
Contains only approximately 75 calories per serving without croutons.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break off broccoli florets.
Cook and drain bacon; break up into smaller pieces.
Mix the first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour dressing mixture in along with nuts and mix thoroughly.
Let stand at least 8 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: cys butter barbecue sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, melt butter; add onion and saute until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Sauce keeps well in refrigerator.
Warm before using.
Makes 2 cups.

title: christmas punch
directions: Makes 1 large bowl punch.

title: philly beef dip
directions: Mix all together well and chill.

title: cheesy tuna bunwiches
directions: Combine ingredients and toss lightly.
Spread split hamburger buns with softened margarine (8 to 10 buns); then the filling. Wrap securely in foil.
Place on a baking sheet and heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: egg rolls (lumpia)
directions: Brown beef.
Drain grease.
Brown garlic; add onions until transparent.
Add carrots and green beans to meat mixture. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Add Chinese cabbage and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry; add green onions.
When cooked, put in colander to drain.
Let meat mixture cool before putting into wrapper.
Makes approximately 100 egg rolls.

title: star sandwich appetizer
directions: Combine Bisquick, onion, parsley, sage and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Mix and roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out 16 stars.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove; brush with melted butter and cool.
Split in half.
Spread top half with mustard.
Place turkey and greens on bottom.
Put together and serve.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Add honey, milk, Egg Beaters and oil to bowl.
Fill baking cups.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes at 425°.

title: red punch
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on the package.
Let cool before adding to other ingredients.
Mix Kool-Aid, water, sugar, pineapple juice and cooled Jell-O together and chill.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.

title: green beans au gratin
directions: Cook green beans following directions on package.
Drain and reserve.
Melt butter in frying pan and saute onion until golden brown.
Gradually stir in flour, water, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Combine with beans and sour cream. Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 3 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, then pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: indoor smores
directions: Butter 9 x 9-inch pan.
Heat to boiling oleo and white karo syrup, remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla, stir until chocolate melts.
Fold in Golden grahams cereal until completely coated.
Add mini marshmallows.
Press into pan.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: nacho fondue
directions: In
1/2 quart saucepan stir soup.
Stir in cheese and milk. Heat over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth and
bubbling,
stirring
constantly.
Stir
in
salsa, remove from
heat.
Serve
in
fondue pot with chips, bread or fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sausage and egg quiche
directions: Fry sausage and onion.
Drain.
Mix sausage and onion with rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Let it set all day or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in hot cast-iron skillet.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs(appetizers)
directions: Combine chili sauce and jelly in crock-pot.
Set at medium heat.
After jelly melts, add meatballs.
Continue cooking until meatballs are hot.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With sharp knife cut beef across grain into thin strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned. If not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat. Increase heat.
Add vegetables; toss until vegetables are crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to mixture; stir.
Cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat thoroughly. Serves 4. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: cheese stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash.
Blend yolks with cheese spread, chili peppers and salt.
Refill egg whites with yolk mixture and sprinkle each with paprika.
Chill.

title: mexican chili dip
directions: Layer in order listed in a quiche or 6 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle a little more shredded cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with large corn chips.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onion together.
Drain.
Combine sausage, onions and other ingredients.
Mix well. Chill overnight. Shape into balls. Roll in flour, dip in beaten egg and then bread crumbs. Deep fry until golden brown.
Makes 45 to 50 bite size balls.

title: thymed vegetables
directions: Melt butter.
Add thyme and salt, then all other ingredients. Mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Beat oranges, cake mix, cooking oil and eggs (1 at a time) all together.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° about 15 minutes or until done.
Chill in refrigerator before frosting

title: grandma salzer's dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers into quart jars.
Boil first 4 ingredients. Place dill in top and bottom of each jar.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers.
Add 1/4 teaspoon alum.
Seal.

title: drumstick dessert
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Add wafers and peanuts, reserving some peanuts to sprinkle on top.

title: nancy's zucchini bread
directions: To beaten eggs, add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend.
Turn into greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel pears, quarter and grind in chopper.
Drain juice.
Put a gallon of ground pears to 1/2 gallon of sugar.
Add crushed pineapple.
Cook for 1hour or until juice is thick.
Add lemon juice (optional).
Seal while hot.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple until the pineapple turns green. Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Turn mixture into shallow dish and chill thoroughly (several hours or overnight) before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening with the sugar and eggs. Cut in bananas. Add flour and nuts.
Heat oven to 330° and bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups. Boil and stir in jello until dissolved.
Refrigerate until thick. Whip or put in blender.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts. Chill to set.

title: great sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, flour and Worcestershire sauce until blended. Form balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
After browning, you can keep these in freezer bags and freeze for later use.
These are good at breakfast or anytime.
Delicious just to snack on.
Enjoy!

title: yellow cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour two (8 x 1 1/2 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch) round baking pans.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until well combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Turn into pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Bring salt and water to a boil, then add vegetables and simmer 5 minutes.
Reserve.
Heat milk and broth to a boil.
Melt butter in second pot over low heat.
Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in flour and blend.
Cool.
Gradually add hot milk and broth, stirring constantly until thick.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in vegetables with liquid.
Add crumbled bacon, grated cheese and mustard.
Season with salt and cayenne pepper.

title: chili
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large pot.
Stir in black pepper, salt and chili powder.
Add more to taste.
Sprinkle garlic powder over whole top until white.
Stir in.
Cook until well done.
Add kidney beans.

title: slush mix
directions: Boil sugar and water.
In large half gallon pail or container, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in freezer and stir occasionally for 2 days before serving.
Mixture will freeze into a "slush" that can be scooped with ice cream scoop into glasses.
Add 7-Up or Squirt and it's a tasty holiday beverage.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add the butter and the milk.
Bake in a casserole dish. Set in a pan of water in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until the top of the pudding is firm like a custard.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and mix in flour.
Stir in walnuts.
Place teaspoonfuls of dough on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus congealed salad
directions: Mix sugar, water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add juice from asparagus, salt and Knox gelatine that has been soaked in 1/2 cup cold water.
Put in cold water and let congeal slightly.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown hamburger; saute onions.
Cook and crumble bacon. Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add Coke just before adding sauce to cooked meat.

title: tasty pinto beans
directions: Soak beans in water for 8 hours. Spray a large dutch oven with cooking spray. Add vegetables and saute until tender. Drain beans and add to vegetables. Cover with fresh water. Add all seasonings; bring to a rolling boil and reduce heat to simmering. Check often and add water if necessary. Cook 2 to 3 hours or until tender. During the last hour, add ham chunks or sausage that has been cut up. Serve with rice and cornbread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken using seasoning.
When done (25 to 30 minutes), take chicken out to cool.
Save broth.
Dip out 1 cup broth for later and boil noodles in broth for 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: german bologna bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in saucepan melt butter.
Add onion, celery, salt, caraway seed and pepper; saute until tender.
Stir in noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and bologna.
Pour into casserole. Spread top of casserole with shredded cheese.
Pour eggs over all. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow casserole to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Garnish with bologna slices, if desired.

title: peggy's broccoli casserole
directions: With Cheddar cheese on top, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine crumbled cornbread with rest of items and chill overnight.

title: broiled salmon with dill sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan on low heat; add lemon juice. Spray broiler pan with nonstick vegetable spray. Brush salmon on both sides with lemon butter and put, skin side down, on prepared pan. Measure thickest part and broil 10 minutes per inch.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put butter in pan.
Add minced onions until clear.
Add ketchup, Miracle Whip, sugar, mustard, vinegar, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer until sauce begins to thicken, approximately 1 hour.
Heat jars and fill while sauce is hot.
Secure cap and let cool.
Will keep indefinitely if refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with the graham cracker crust; set aside.
Beat cream cheese and peanut butter until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar; beat until smooth.
Add milk gradually; beat again.
Fold in whipped topping, then pour into prepared crust. Freeze overnight and remove when ready to serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together melted oleo, flour and chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; pour over the crust. Mix the pudding and milk; then spread on top of the cream cheese layer.
Put rest of the Cool Whip on top.
Ready to serve.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute the onion in butter. Stir in ground beef, garlic, flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Saute 5 minutes and remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and soup.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: pot de creme(serves 4 to 5)
directions: Put everything in the blender except the cream.
Liquify in blender.
Heat the cream to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour cream into blender.
Blend very well until all ingredients are mixed.
Pour into sherbets about half full.
Chill this, top with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Take one can of crescent rolls and press firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla flavoring and pour on top of first layer.
Take second can of rolls and pinch together on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate before cutting.

title: chicken salad
directions: Remove bones, gristle, fat and skin from cooked meat.
Cut meat into 1/2-inch cubes and mix with an equal amount of celery pieces. Moisten with French dressing.
Add mayonnaise dressing to taste. Arrange on lettuce leaves; garnish with curled celery.

title: tom's chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter; mix in powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Make into balls.
Put in freezer.
Dip in melted wax and chocolate chips.
Put in freezer.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in margarine.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place in a single layer in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pretend soup
directions: Put 2 cups orange juice in bowl, add yogurt, honey and lemon juice; whisk together.
In each bowl:
add 5 slices banana and 2 tablespoons berries.
Ladle soup on top of fruit.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Eat.

title: chewy skor toffee bits cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl until well blended.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture. Beat until well blended.
Stir in toffee bits.
Drop by rounded tsp. onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 9 - 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack and cool completely.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour popcorn
directions: Set popcorn aside.
Combine ingredients over low heat until butter/margarine melts and sugar dissolves.
Drizzle over popcorn and bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Keeps 2 weeks in a sealed container.

title: fruited chicken-en-creme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat butter and oil in baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in baking dish. Bake 1 hour.
Heat soup, cream and sherry in saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Stir pineapple, grapes and mushrooms into soup mixture.
Remove baking dish from oven, drain off fat.
Pour soup-fruit mixture over chicken.
Cover baking dish with aluminum foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
If desired, garnish with clusters of green grapes. Yields 6 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Whip corn bread, bread and broth together with wire whip until smooth as cornbread batter.
Add sage and salt.
Whip eggs.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to mix.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, eggs and beat together well. Add vanilla, water and mix. Add next 3 dry ingredients and blend. Mix in coconut and chocolate chips. Grease a 9x13 pan. Bake 20-25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: almond cream puff ring
directions: About 3 hours before serving, in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat water, butter or margarine and salt until butter melts and mixture boils.
Remove saucepan from heat.
With wooden spoon, vigorously stir in flour all at once until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of saucepan.
Add eggs to flour mixture, one at a time, beating after each addition, until mixture is smooth and satiny.
Cool mixture slightly.
Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease and flour large cookie sheet.
Using 7-inch plate as a guide, trace a circle in flour on cookie sheet.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into 10 mounds, inside circle, to form a ring.
Bake ring 40 minutes or until golden.
Turn off oven; let ring remain in oven 15 minutes.
Remove ring from oven; cool on wire rack.
When ring is cool, with long serrated knife, slice horizontally in half.
Prepare Almond-Cream Filling; spoon into bottom of ring.
Replace top of ring.
Refrigerate.
Prepare Chocolate Glaze.
Spoon glaze over top of ring.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add blackberries and buttermilk.
Sift flour, spices and soda into mixture.
Add eggs and brown sugar; beat until smooth.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk 3 or 4 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well and spread in buttered pan.

title: company's coming pie
directions: Grease large pie pan or plate.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 cup sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with other crust.
Crimp edges.
Slit top.
Brush with egg, if desired. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle toppings.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
They will be chewy if not overbeaten or overbaked.

title: strawberry rhubarb jello
directions: To cook rhubarb in microwave:
Add 1 tablespoon water to 3 cups diced rhubarb and cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: annie wingate's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until it falls from bone.
Remove from stock and allow to cool.
Boil spaghetti in remaining chicken stock.
Cook celery and onion in oleo in a 3-quart saucepan using low heat. Add 1 pint stock and simmer 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup slowly; add cheese slowly.
Stir in the boiled and rinsed spaghetti.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add shredded chicken and stuffed olives.
Add the seasonings and mix well.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Heat, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 generously.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, pecans and butter together.
Press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Mix 10x sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together and pour over crust.
Whip milk and pudding together.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: fiesta ketchup
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients. Pulse the mixture several times to mix. Scrape down the sides of the bowl and process until the mixture is well blended, about 30 seconds. Put in your container. Refrigerate and use as desired.

title: crock-pot fajitos
directions: Cut steak into medium portions. In crock-pot, combine meat, onion, peppers (green, red and jalapeno), cilantro, chili powder, cumin, garlic, coriander and salt. Add tomatoes. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high about 4 hours or until meat is tender. After cooking, shred meat and return to mixture and serve hot. To serve, spread mixture on tortillas. Add desired toppings. Roll up tortillas and serve.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with chicken in bite size pieces.
Mix soup, broth, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with cheese. Brown 4 cups of corn flakes with 1/2 stick butter.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until sauce bubbles through the corn flakes.

title: knox blox
directions: *Sugar-free Jell-O is okay.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Pour dry cake mix and sugar into a large mixing bowl.
Add apricot nectar and oil.
Mix, adding eggs one at a time, mixing after each.
Bake in an angel food cake pan (greased and floured) in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Let cake cool.
Remove cake from pan by running knife blade around outer cake pan and center post.
Cover with glaze or leave plain.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil hard for about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until creamy and almost cool.
Pour on buttered platter or cookie sheet.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Combine butter, flour and milk to make sauce. Set aside. Combine the tomato paste, cream cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly.
Add to sauce mixture and cook until cheese is melted.
Add salmon. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water or white wine.
Add to salmon mixture. Place in lightly greased mold and refrigerate.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Place all ingredients in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until liquid is absorbed.

title: tipsy sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients except topping. Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with pecans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage head in boiling water, drain, and cool. Peel leaves carefully.
Brown meat along with onion and bell pepper. Drain well. Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add tomato sauce, cheese soup and uncooked rice.
Simmer 10-15 minutes.
Fill cabbage leaves with portion of sauce.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour remaining sauce on top. These can be frozen for later use.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Gradually add evaporated milk. Heat
in
a
saucepan
over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
When mixture is about to boil, add syrup and vanilla. Beat
until mixture is glassy and smooth.
Store in closed container.
No refrigeration is necessary.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Grind vegetables in a meat grinder using the coarsest blade. Combine all vegetables in a large bowl; sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain thoroughly in a colander, then press out all liquid.
Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil, stir in vegetables and simmer 10 minutes.
Immediately pack into clean, hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space; seal.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yield:
about 6 pints.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into refrigerator until it gels.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut medium head cabbage in Pyrex dish.
Put onion on top. Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over cabbage and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup (or mushroom) and egg together. Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter on crackers.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cornbread, maybe some beans.

title: spinach pie
directions: Blanch, drain and chop spinach.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter and saute onion until tender.
Add green onion and saute another 2 minutes.
Mix in parsley, dill, cheese, nutmeg, salt, pepper, spinach and beaten eggs.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt
margarine and Cheez Whiz together in microwave or saucepan.
Stir
canned vegetables into this mixture.
Crumble on stack
(35	to
crackers
into the vegetable mixture, reserving a few to crumble on top.	Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in greased pan.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: colorful creative salt
