directions: Add food coloring to salt.
Stir well.
Cook in microwave for 1 to 2 minutes or spread on waxed paper and let air dry.
Store in an airtight container.
Use as you would glitter.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add extract, then add 1 1/2 cups flour with soda and salt sifted in.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour with milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue onions
directions: Simmer all ingredients, but onions, for 45 minutes.
Add onions and cook 3 more minutes.

title: honey pie
directions: In a saucepan, bring honey to a boil.
Quickly beat eggs into honey; add butter, vanilla, nuts and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until filling is set.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook beans in crock-pot until almost done.
Saute venison and onions.
Add chili powder, cumin powder, garlic salt, salt and pepper, all to taste.
Pour meat mixture into beans.
Pour tomato juice over this.
Let cook overnight or all day. Serve with corn bread muffins.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook apple juice, cornstarch and cinnamon until thick and clear.
Pour over apples in pie shell.
Cover with top shell and bake for 40 minutes at 425°.
Yield:
1 pie.

title: hot pepper and veggie mix
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook all together 5 minutes or until peppers and veggies change color.
Put in canning jars and seal.
Make sure you have the chili peppers in each jar or it will be too hot.
Makes 4 or 5 quarts.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll thin about 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut in strips, about 1/2-inch wide.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in double boiler until thick, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Add juice and grated rind of lemon. Whipped cream can be added before serving over your favorite fruit.

title: savory green beans
directions: Heat beans in saucepan; drain well.
Add butter.
Place in shallow serving dish.
Sprinkle with vinegar.
Toss with cheese and croutons.
Serve immediately.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight. Rinse. Cover with water in heavy pot. Add ham bone (fat trimmed off) and remaining ingredients, except sausage and rice.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add sausage (which has been steamed in skillet, drained and fried).
Just before serving, remove bay leaf and add a little more fresh parsley. For added thickness, remove about a cup of beans from the pot, mash thoroughly and return to mixture.
Serve with boiled rice and garnish with scallions. Serves 8.

title: meme's hash and biscuits
directions: I use leftover roast and cut it up in small chunks.
Chop 3 to 4 potatoes in cubes and boil with salt and pepper; don't overcook. Saute 1 large onion in butter in a large black skillet.
Add potatoes.
Use the juice to make gravy or get a brown gravy mix and use to thicken.
Add meat last.
Bake biscuits separately and split open, then pour hash on top.

title: four-way layered delight
directions: Mix instant pudding until very thick.
Put half in a bowl. Then put the graham crackers over the pudding.
Slice the banana and layer it over the crackers.
Then put the pineapple over the bananas.
Then put a layer of sliced strawberries over the pineapple. Then put the rest of the pudding mix over the strawberries and spread well.
Put in the refrigerator and chill well until ready to serve.

title: basic blender crepes
directions: Add all ingredients to blender jar.
Cover and process at stir speed until blended, 20 to 25 seconds.
Scrape down flour on sides of jar; blend 5 seconds more.
Heat a 7-inch slope sided lightly-greased skillet over medium-high heat until water drop dances when sprinkled on it (or use electric crepe maker).
Pour 2 tablespoons batter at a time into skillet.
Quickly tilt skillet to cover bottom.
Pour off extra batter into blender jar.
Brown on first side about 1/2 minute; turn to brown on second side.
Stack with wax paper between every 4 crepes.
Place in plastic bag until ready to fill.
These can be refrigerated or frozen.

title: easy fruit cobblerspringfield, missouri
directions: Line bottom of 9 X 13-inch dish with pie dough

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
In a casserole dish, layer half of ground beef, half of onion, half of French fries and salt and pepper.
Mix soups and a can of water.
Pour half over layer.
Repeat layers and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press in bottom of 13 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions and spread over crust.
Slice bananas over mixture; spread pineapple over the bananas and then spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bananas will not turn dark.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, press a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that have been dipped in water.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Let cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then move to racks to finish cooling.
Yield 4 to 5 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: When thickened, add 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup coconut. Dribble this mixture over batter and then bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: doggie biscuits
directions: Beat all liquid ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients. Roll out with flour to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with your pooches favorite cookie cutter shapes.
Bake at 400 for 20 minutes.
Turn off oven, let them cool in oven.
They will dry out as they cool.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1 tablespoon sugar together.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Refrigerate.

title: southern "fried" corn
directions: Clean and desilk corn.
Scrape corn from stalks.
Get all milk and pulp out.
Melt butter and bacon drippings in large skillet. Add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes until corn thickens and is tender.
Add more milk if too thick.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Boil 1 minute; cool.
May add blue food coloring.
Pour over blueberries.
Makes 3 pies.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Dissolve gelatin in hot pineapple.
Add buttermilk.
Place in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in 8 oz. of whipped topping.
Toasted pecans can be added if desired.
Pour the mixture into a mold that has been sprayed with PAM and refrigerate until firm.
(Peach and apricot gelatin make the prettiest salads.)

title: chicken with rice
directions: Cook peppers and onions in oil on low heat until tender, not brown.
Blend cornstarch with small amount of stock and soy sauce. Gently stir chicken and stock into vegetables.
Cook and stir until clear and thickened.
Add tomatoes and continue cooking at medium heat until tomatoes blend and are hot.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dietetic cranberry punch
directions: Combine juices and sweetener.
Chill and stir in ginger ale, which has been chilled.
Just before serving add ice cubes.

title: pickle cucumbers
directions: Slice onion and cucumbers.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and grated clove.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put in jar and let stand for 24 hours.

title: chocolate dessert waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron. Sift flour, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/2 cup sugar and cocoa. Separate the yolks and whites. Beat the egg yolks and add 1 1/2 cups milk and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Beat smooth. Add oil and mix. Beat the egg whites with clean dry beaters until stiff. Then fold into the waffles. Bake in waffle iron. Make the glaze dip.

title: never fail crisp dill pickles
directions: Put cucumbers that were washed into a quart jar with a piece of dill in each jar.
Put in the salt, sugar and vinegar.
Fill with water to top of jar to 1/2-inch of top.
Clean top of jar and place jar cap on tight and place jars into kettle of cool water so jars are covered over the top.
Bring to boiling point and pickles will turn color.
Take jars out and tighten tops, if necessary.
This recipe makes only one quart.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, drain.
Make gravy mix according to package.
In 9x13 baking pan, layer meat, gravy mix, then layer sliced cheese and top with tater tots.
Bake at 350 degrees until tater tots are golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter in bowl.
Add sugars gradually and mix well.
Stir in eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork, dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool on wire rack. Yields 6 dozen.

title: barbecue burger cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and onions until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Lightly grease 10 muffin cups. Press an uncooked biscuit in each of the 10 cups.
Bring dough up to the rims.
Spoon meat mixture into the biscuit-lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Add remainder of ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes until set.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 250° until crisp.

title: cake donuts
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands in a large bowl.
Put on floured board and knead until soft.
Roll out to 1/2 inch and cut. Fry 3 minutes in hot oil, turning when it comes to the top. Drain on brown paper bag.
Shake in sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: 7 week bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup All-Bran and boiling water and set aside to cool.
When cooled, add Wesson oil and set aside again.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk and 2 cups All-Bran.
Pour first bran mixture into second mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: witches' brew
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in hot water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Heat thoroughly but do not allow to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cloves.

title: pennsylvania dutch pancakes
directions: Mix well and fry in a hot skillet at 400° (electric).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain and mash. Beat together eggs and milk; add to squash. Mix cheese, oleo and cracker crumbs. Add 1/2 of this to casserole mixture. Put into buttered casserole and top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: paska(slovak easter bread)
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan; heat until warm.
Crumble yeast into mixture.
Stir in eggs (these must be room temperature).
Add melted butter and 4 to 5 drops food coloring.
Mix in flour, first with spoon and then with hand.
Add flour in 2 additions.
When dough begins to leave sides of bowl, turn it out onto floured board and knead.

title: parisian french toast
directions: Slice French bread on an angle until entire loaf is cut. Mix eggs with the coffee lightener. Dip the bread on both sides in the eggs and fry in margarine. Place on plate with fruit, butter or syrup and enjoy.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken and vegetables in dish.
Stir together soup, chicken broth and pepper.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Combine flour, milk and oleo; stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: double divinity
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until firm ball will form in cold water.
Pour over egg whites and 1/2 of the syrup.
Place remaining syrup over the stove and cook until crack stage when dropped in cold water.
Pour this over the egg white mixture which you have beaten while syrup is cooking.
Beat until creamy and add nuts and flavoring. When cool, drop by spoonfuls on oil paper or buttered platter, or pour onto buttered platter and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: red hot salad
directions: Cook 1 cup water and candies on stove until candies dissolve. Remove and add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water. Stir.
Refrigerate until starts to set.
Add pineapple, celery, apples and nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate until set.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: In a very large bowl, mix first four ingredients (squash, onions and peppers) well and sprinkle with the salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and wash with cold water in a colander.
After washing, boil together the vinegar, pickling spice and celery seed.
(Tie spice and celery seed in a clean white cloth.)
Strain and add sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Put in squash mixture and boil to a good hard boil.
Pack in pint jars and seal. Yields 6 pints.

title: apple or cherry crisp
directions: Place in 9 x 13-inch pan in preceding order.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use whipped cream for topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours or 2 to 3 hours on high setting.

title: microwave bean bake
directions: Chop bacon and cook in glass casserole in microwave.
Add chopped onion; cook until soft (about 4 minutes).
Stir in rest of ingredients and cover.
Microwave on Medium power about 45 minutes; stir every 15 minutes.
Adjust time according to your microwave.

title: berry custard pie
directions: Make a regular custard. Put the berries in crust to cover the bottom, at least a cup. Some berries take more sugar than others, just guess. Sprinkle 1/4 cup more sugar over them. Pour the custard over the berries. If you are using a juicy berry like blackberry, either stir a teaspoon of flour into the sugar or use a little less milk in the custard. Don't bake custard in as hot an oven as other pie.

title: scotch cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Pour cocoa mixture over this and blend.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into sheet cake pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Ice while hot with icing

title: ruth's round up bean casserole
directions: Brown beef; season with salt and pepper.
Add onion and green pepper.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
This can also be cooked in a slow pot.
Serve with salad and cornbread.

title: chip-n-dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage and then drain.
Put meat into crock-pot.
Add cheese, milk, soup and garlic to taste.
Cook on high until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Stir sugar, milk and flour together.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour batter over butter and put fruit of your choice on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Cook the pumpkin, then mix all ingredients together.
Serve either warm or chilled.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Partly steam fresh cut up broccoli (until it's still crunchy). Cut up and cook bacon; drain.
Add to broccoli with cheese and onion.
Mix 1 package of Good Seasons salad dressing as directed plus 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over salad and toss.
Good served warm or cold.

title: citrus dessert salad
directions: Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sugar, spice, milk, egg and pumpkin in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a "full" bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool five minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into shell and chill four hours.

title: pop's cranberry salad
directions: Pour sugar over ground cranberries.
Let set for 2 hours.
Mix jello in 1 cup hot water.
Drain pineapple.
Add nuts, jello, apple, pineapple and sugar with cranberries.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in refrigerator to congeal.
Prepare cream cheese with enough milk to form whip cream consistency.
Spread on congealed portion of mixture and return to refrigerator.
Eat when salad is cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or lightly brown.

title: caramel crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Combine crackers and nuts in a large bowl. In a sauce pan, bring butter, sugar, and corn syrup to a boil and cook 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter and date logs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almond bark.
Form mixture into logs.
Let stand in freezer until firm.
Melt almond bark and dip logs into bark to cover.
Place on wax paper until set.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and mayonnaise.
Add milk.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: art's snack mix
directions: *Regular stick margarine will not blend well with sauce.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor.
Stir in the sugar to blend. Set aside. Dissolve gelatin dessert in water. Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Add oranges, nuts and pineapple.
Stir well.
Pour into lightly oiled 8-cup mold. Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve on plate of crisp green lettuce.
Yields 16 servings.

title: diabetic semi-sweet dipping chocolate
directions: Combine milk powder, cocoa and wax in food processor or blender; blend to soft powder.
Add shortening.
Place over hot water and cook until wax is completely dissolved and mixture is thick, smooth and creamy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar replacement and let cool slightly.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cocoa and baking powder.
In medium-size bowl with wooden spoon, beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in eggs and milk.
Add peanut butter mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until well combined.
Spread into greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Cut into 30 or less squares.

title: tallyrina
directions: Saute meat.
Remove from skillet, draining well.
Saute onions, peppers and garlic in same drippings.
Mix with meat.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco Bran.
(I add margarine to this so it melts or softens good.)
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients, except Kellogg's All-Bran.
Mix well.
Last of all, stir in Kellogg's All-Bran.

title: fresh coconut cakes
directions: Mix together
and bake in Bundt pan in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Can
bake
two cakes at same time by doubling recipe except the oil, pecans, vanilla and milk.
Will make one Bundt and one angel food cake.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together as listed in order, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Makes a delicious deep dark chocolate cake.
Very moist and wonderful served with chocolate pudding or Cool Whip.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut in 2 layers after cooled.

title: no wait yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water, then add sugar, salt, oil and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in flour.
Bake in muffin tins (small size) for approximately 20 minutes at 400°.
Can store remaining batter for up to a week in refrigerator.

title: chicken breasts lombardy
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and set mushrooms aside.
Cut each chicken breast half in half lengthwise.
Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/8 inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour.

Place 5 to 6 pieces of chicken in 1 to 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet; cook over medium heat 3 or 4 minutes on each side or until golden. Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or other large casserole, overlapping edges.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken and butter.
Reserve pan drippings in skillet. Sprinkle reserved mushrooms over chicken.
Add wine and broth to reserved pan drippings in skillet.
Bring to a boil, simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Pour sauce evenly over chicken.
Combine cheeses and green onions; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Broil 6 inches from heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shake and bake chicken and potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Coat potatoes and chicken with Shake 'n Bake.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour in pot until thick. when thickened and while still hot add 1 stick margarine.
Set aside. Let Cool.
Cut up 4 medium apples.
Put apples and 1 cup chopped nuts into pineapple mixture.
Top with medium container of cool whip (8 oz. size).

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together all but milk; then add enough milk to make a thick dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil until browned well.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve warm.

title: ham-pineapple rolls
directions: Drain pineapple, measuring syrup and adding enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, substituting juice liquid for water and adding crushed pineapple to stuffing crumbs.
Spoon about 1/4 cup stuffing on each ham slice.
Roll up and place seam side down in melted butter in a skillet.
Heat, uncovered, turning occasionally.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, alternating with flour, milk and flavoring.
Add salt.
Bake at 325° for about 90 minutes or longer in a Bundt pan.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Meanwhile, heat butter and cream over low heat until butter is melted.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Keep warm over low heat.
Drain noodles and return to pot.
Pour sauce over noodles and toss gently until noodles are well coated with sauce.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Cook rhubarb and 1 cup of sugar until tender, 5 to 8 minutes. Cream 1/2 cup of sugar and shortening.
Add egg, vanilla and milk. Add flour-baking powder mixture.
Pour rhubarb into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes and turn upside down.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Spread center of a 20-inch sheet of foil with butter.
Cut steak in small serving pieces.
Arrange on foil, slightly overlapping pieces.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, green pepper and tomatoes.
Season.
Mix juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Seal foil tightly. Bake 2 hours to serve.
Roll back foil and sprinkle with parsley.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook beef in drippings for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Mix with remaining ingredients and turn into a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy pumpkin soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat thoroughly without boiling.
Serve with croutons.

title: sour cream rhubarb squares
directions: Mix sugar, nuts, butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Set aside.
Cream brown sugar, egg and shortening.
Then sift in flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, sour cream and stir in rhubarb.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased angel food pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Drizzle with frosting.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Add soda, salt, ginger, cloves and cinnamon and mix well.
Add flour and cream until smooth.

title: date nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in walnuts and dates.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° (slow oven) until top has dull crust, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares, cool.
Remove from pan.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: grandma's drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs, vanilla, butter or margarine and buttermilk or sour milk.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and cream of tartar.
Add dry ingredient mixture to wet mixture in parts. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
May decorate for holiday baking with sprinkles. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: herman pan biscuits
directions: Mix and put into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: summer fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, stir together graham crackers, margarine and sugar until well blended.
Press crumbs mixture into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
In a small saucepan, stir together jelly and water.
Cook over low heat for 3 minutes. Arrange fruit over baked crust.
Drizzle jelly mixture over fruit. Serve either chilled or at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Mix in baking dish: sugar, flour, milk and 1/2 of melted butter.
Pour fruit in the middle of the baking dish and spread to sides.
Do not stir.
Add remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pancakes for a crowd
directions: Add soda, sugar and salt to buttermilk in large bowl.
Sift flour and baking powder and mix into first ingredients.
Add yeast, oil, cream and eggs.
Mix well.
Store overnight in refrigerator.

title: holiday cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese; stir in crushed pineapple, pecans (1 cup), green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Form into balls and roll in 1 cup pecans.
Chill until serving.
Garnish with pineapple slices and maraschino cherries.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and set aside.
In a separate bowl combine the eggs, sugar, and vanilla, beating well. Mix in the zucchini and carrots.
Combine with the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir in the nuts and the bran flakes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2-inch by 4 1/2-inch by 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cheese pie
directions: Mix together eggs, onion and jalapenos.
Add cheese and mix well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup to boiling
and
mix	with cream cheese until melted.
Mix gelatin in
water and add to mixture.	Cool.
Add shrimp, celery and onions
to mixture.
Fold in mayonnaise and chill until set.

title: quick and easy french toast
directions: Mix egg, milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon together.
Dip bread in mixture and brown on both sides in hot buttered skillet.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage;	wash,
cook
and
drain rice.
Mix sausage, rice
and
all other ingredients, except almonds.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
During last 15 minutes, add slivered almonds on top.
Cover and return to oven.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In skillet, lightly brown beef, onions and bell pepper. Season at this point.
Drain ground beef.
Put in paste, salt, sugar, garlic powder and pepper.
Add water and simmer 30 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into a 5-quart ice cream churn. Any fruit may be added to mixture.

title: ham and sweet potato roll
directions: Combine ingredients, except sweet potatoes.

Spread on wax paper to 1/2-inch thick, making a rectangle about 6 x 10-inches. Spread with seasoned sweet potatoes and roll like a jelly roll. Place in dripping pan and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix together graham crackers, sugar and butter and line 9 x 13-inch pan with it.
Beat together eggs, cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, cover with blueberry pie filling. Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: taco soup(low-fat - high fiber)
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain. Transfer to Dutch oven or large saucepan. Mix Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix and taco seasoning mix into meat. Then, without draining, add all other of the ingredients. Simmer one hour.

title: north pole soup
directions: Saute onion and carrot in olive oil for 5 minutes. Add garlic, ham and basil. Saute 2 more minutes. Add the tomatoes, chicken broth, kidney beans, salt and pepper. Cook 20 minutes. Add the pasta and cook 6 more minutes. Serve with parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: pink lemonade dessert
directions: Mix wafers, butter and sugar in bottom of serving dish. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chunky beef soup
directions: In a large pot, brown beef and onions. Drain fat. Add tomato juice and all other ingredients. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes then add 1/2 cup either elbow macaroni or barley** Cook until tender. If soup is too thick add 1-cup additional beef bouillon.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 (3 ounce) package strawberry jello.
Pour over fresh strawberries in cooled and baked crust.

title: sweet potatoes yams
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Simmer on stove in pan the brown sugar, oleo, salt and water for 10 minutes.
Place apples, nuts and potatoes in baking dish.
Put marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown on top.

title: light italian spaghetti primavera
directions: Prepare Creamette thin spaghetti as package directs; drain. In large skillet, combine remaining ingredients except cheese and parsley.
Simmer just until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti; sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: delicious cabbage
directions: Brown onion in bacon fat.
Remove onions from pan.
Place 1/3 of the sliced cabbage in pan, followed by half of bell pepper, one tomato and half the brown onion.
Layer with another 1/3 of cabbage and remaining bell pepper, tomato and onion.
Sprinkle in remaining cabbage and cook for an additional 20 minutes or until tender.

title: potato salad with eggs
directions: Mix potatoes lightly with French dressing.
Season with salt, pepper and cayenne to taste.
Add celery, pickles, mayonnaise and chopped egg whites.
Add more seasoning if needed.
Just before serving, garnish with parsley and egg yolks forced through a ricer or sieve.

title: cherry fudge cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie filling and Dream Whip. Beat 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cool.
Spread with pie filling.
Top with Dream Whip. Refrigerate.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour int pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway come out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger, then drain grease.
Add Velveeta by cutting up in chunks.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and onion. Cook until all cheeses have melted and everything is well blended. Serve with nacho chips.

title: unusual corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook the rice until tender (about 45 minutes).
Meanwhile, cook the sliced onions in the butter until tender.
Add the remaining
ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf and cloves and add the rice.
Turn into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy sunday chicken dinner
directions: Mix raw rice, soups and water in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Place chicken on top and sprinkle dry onion soup
mix on top. Seal tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil the last 30 minutes of baking time.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add ingredients by layers in this order, butter, crumbs, coconut, chips, milk and pecans.
Bake
at
325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: debbie's caramel pecan turtles
directions: Melt candy in water in top of a double boiler.
Arrange 36 groups of 4 pecans each, 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Drop 1 teaspoon of hot caramel on each group.
Cool 15 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and spoon 1 teaspoon on each turtle.
Cool in a dry place.
Makes 36 turtles.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add vanilla and almond to butter mixture, then add flour mixture, a little at a time until all used up.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water; cool.
Add the drained pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Chill in large glass bowl or pan until firm.
Heat the pineapple juice in top of double boiler. Combine sugar, flour and egg and add to the hot pineapple juice and cook until thick, stirring constantly.

Cool, then fold in the whipped cream, stirring just until ingredients are blended. Spread over chilled gelatin mixture and top with grated cheese. Continue chilling until topping is also firm before serving.

title: fruit in a cone
directions: Put about 3/4 cup of cut up fruit (enough to fill rim).
Choose from any of these fruits:
strawberries, bananas, apples, blueberries, raspberries, pears or grapes.
Drizzle with 1 teaspoon of honey and sprinkle it with 1 teaspoon granola.
Makes 1 cone.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix equal parts of cranberry juice and 7-Up.
Garnish with sherbet.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put in long baking dish in oven and bake until the fruit bubbles (at 350°).
On top of the fruit, put the rolls from a tube of unbaked rolls.
Bake about 12 minutes or until rolls are getting brown.

title: crescent roll-ups
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with onion salt and bacon.
Cut each roll lengthwise into 3 equal wedges.
Roll up each, starting at point of wedge.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 2 dozen.

title: vegetable oil substitute
directions: Substitute an equal amount of applesauce for the vegetable oil in cookies, cakes and breads.
A 1/3 cup substitution of natural applesauce for 1/3 cup of vegetable oil will eliminate 602 calories and 72 grams of fat in the whole recipe.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soak the Knox gelatine in 3/4 cup cold water.
Add hot mixture to gelatin and stir well.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Let stand for a while and add chopped apples, chopped celery and pecans.
Chill.

title: holiday dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler or soften in microwave. Add all other ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Serve from chafing dish with crackers or vegetables.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in skillet; saute onions and celery.
Add beef and brown.
Season with savory and salt.
Drain excess fat.
Place meat mixture in casserole dish.
Pour corn over meat.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add chili mix (chop it up) and tomato sauce; heat.
Add cubes of cheese; stir until melted. Serve with taco chips or veggies.
Works as a meal.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until medium soft, slice into large bowl.
Add diced green and red peppers and celery; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well.
Squeeze, if necessary.
Grate Jack cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Place mixture in greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil; remove from heat and place tea bags in water.
Cover and leave 6 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add spices that have been tied in a cloth bag.
Leave 30 minutes. Remove spices and add cherry Jell-O, cranberry juice, apple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 3/4 gallons.

title: party meat balls(microwave)
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Arrange meatballs in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover dish with a paper towel.
Microwave at 100% power for 4 minutes.
Turn meatballs over and microwave 4 minutes longer. Drain.

title: jean's harvest beets
directions: Drain liquid from 1 can beets into small saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients to liquid and cook over low heat until sauce thickens.
Add beets to sauce and continue cooking until beets are hot.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk and sugar.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat until mixture reaches 234° or soft ball stage, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.

title: roast, rice and gravy
directions: Stuff roast with garlic and season it.
Brown it in 1/4 cup grease with onion and bell pepper.
Slowly add water and cook for about 2 hours.
Cook rice, then add your potatoes and carrot to roast for 45 minutes, then you're ready to eat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Leave sausage out
of refrigerator until soft.	Measure Bisquick into large mixing	bowl
and
then
add sausage.
Mix together.
Melt cheese
in	double	boiler	or microwave until melted.
Mix with sausage and Bisquick.
Roll into small balls and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into a 12-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Dollop 1 tablespoon whipped topping on each slice.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Scald the milk.
Add the beaten egg yolks, sugar and gelatin which has been dissolved in the pineapple juice (heat juice and dissolve).
Set aside to cool.
Add pineapple and cut up cherries. Whip the cream and fold into beaten egg whites.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Break angel food cake in pieces and place in pan.
Pour mixture over and chill.
Serve with whipped cream and cherries.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine the blackberry-flavored gelatin with the boiling water.
Pour into salad mold or 9 x 13-inch dish.
When this starts to set, add the blueberry pie filling and crushed pineapple with its juice; let gel.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
When gelatin has set, spread cream cheese mixture over gelatin.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture begins to boil, stirring after 3 minutes.
Mix well.
Scrape bowl.

title: teriyaki flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients in gallon size sealable plastic bag. Seal bag, squeezing out air; turn to coat steak.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, turning bag over occasionally. Prepare grill.
Drain marinade into small saucepan; bring to boil. Simmer 10 minutes and remove from heat.
Grill steak 1 minute on each side; grill 5 to 6 minutes longer on each side for medium-rare or until done to taste, basting frequently with marinade.
Remove to carving board; let stand 10 minutes before carving.
Carve steak diagonally across grain into thin slices. Serve each portion with heated marinade.
Serves 4.

title: mermaid dip
directions: Blend until smooth the soup, cream cheese, garlic powder and Tabasco sauce. Fold in tuna and parsley. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: greek salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, toss together endive and lettuce; mound onto 6 individual salad plates.
Arrange tomatoes, Feta cheese, olives and onions on top of greens.

title: grilled butterflied leg of lamb(like the song, parsley, sage, rosemary and thyme)
directions: Prepare the butterflied leg of lamb by removing all fat and skin.
Place in large, nonreactive enamel pot, dish or casserole. Combine the oil, lemon juice, garlic, bay leaves, parsley sprigs, salt, pepper, sage, rosemary and thyme.
Usually the lamb will be about half covered by the marinade.
Add enough good quality red wine to completely cover the lamb.
Marinate the lamb in this mixture for 24 hours; turn occasionally to distribute marinade evenly.

title: chicken and wild rice(8 servings)
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Firmly pack rice into the bottom of a casserole.
Combine chicken, milk, sherry, soup and almonds.
Cook until heated through.
Pour chicken mixture over rice.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini and corn salad
directions: In a large heavy skillet heat olive oil until hot but not smoking.
Add zucchini and saute, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Add corn and saute for 2 minutes.
Add red wine vinegar and bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: taco dip platter
directions: Spread beans on a 12-inch serving plate.
Layer salsa, guacamole and sour cream, leaving 1-inch around each layer. Sprinkle with chiles, olives and cheeses.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: huckleberry pie
directions: Wash and drain huckleberries.
Simmer together 1 cup huckleberries and 2/3 cup water for 3 minutes.
Blend and add to boiling mixture the sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Save out 1/2 cup of choice huckleberries.
Put remaining 2 1/2 cups of huckleberries in pie shell.
Cover with cooked mixture and garnish with 1/2 cup of remaining huckleberries.
Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip. Great with fresh huckleberries!

title: fancy one crust
directions: Mix together with fork or small food processor.
Press into 9-inch
pan.
Bake until firm at 350°, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake(serves 12)
directions: For Crust:
In a bowl, combine crushed graham crackers and melted margarine.
Press mixture evenly onto bottom and 1 3/4-inches up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan. Place the pan on a baking sheet.
Chill until needed.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, water, vinegar, sugar and turmeric.
Stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour over macaroni and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
The dressing will be runny, but will be absorbed.

title: breakfast ham 'n' cheese pie
directions: In a greased 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate, layer ham, Swiss cheese, bacon, Cheddar cheese, onion and green pepper. Place the remaining ingredients in a blender in the order given; blend for 30 to 40 seconds.
Pour over meat, cheese and vegetables; do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand until soft.
Add onions and 1/2 chopped beef.
Mix well and form a ball.
Roll ball in remaining chopped beef.
Serve with favorite snack crackers.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes on 50% power.
Stir once during cooking time.
When done, stir to blend.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: kim's scalloped potatoes
directions: Place layers of peeled, sliced potatoes and onions with slices of Velveeta and butter pats in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased.
Lay into this some slices of Canadian bacon.
Add layers until pan is 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with flour.
Pour milk over.
Season to taste. Place in 375° oven for approximately 1 1/4 hours (or until bubbly golden on top).
Let stand 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Add enough of the water to make a paste.
Beat in egg yolks well.
Heat remaining water with butter and salt until melted.
Add water mixture to first mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla; stir.
Remove and pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown, or serve with whipped cream.
Be sure to cook in a thick pot.
Triple the recipe to make 4 deep dish pies.

title: chicken casserole(nice for an afternoon luncheon)
directions: Toss all ingredients lightly.
Place in a 10 x 13-inch greased or sprayed cake pan.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese and crumbled Fritos.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions.
When cool, add cream cheese, nuts and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: game hens with spinach-rice stuffing
directions: Prepare Spinach-Rice Stuffing.
With kitchen scissors, cut hens in half lengthwise.
Rinse and pat dry.
Press 3/4 cup of the stuffing onto cut side of each hen half.
Holding stuffing in place with your hand, arrange hens, skin side up, in a greased shallow baking pan.
Melt butter in a small pan over low heat; stir in onion, parsley, mustard and fines herbes.
Brush over hens.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until leg joint moves easily; during last half-hour, baste occasionally with pan drippings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Crush wafers and add melted butter.
Press into an 8-inch pan and save some for top decoration.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl soften yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and half of flour. Mix until smooth.
Add enough of remaining flour to handle easily; mix with hands.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Round up in greased bowl, greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°) until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; let rise again until double (about 30 minutes).
Divide dough in half.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cheese and blend with mayonnaise.
Stir in fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream and tint with food coloring. Place in mold and freeze overnight.
Cut in individual portions about 10 minutes before serving.
This salad will keep for several weeks in freezer.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle topping over the top.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients except margarine and crackers.
Place in greased casserole.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Place on top.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat well.
Sift together next 6 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan which is lined with waxed paper that has been greased. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan by turning over onto a damp towel and let cool.

title: hawaiian ham sandwiches
directions: Combine ham with all ingredients, except bread.
Spread on bread with crusts removed.
Cover with another piece of bread. Cut each sandwich 3 times into finger sandwiches.
Makes about 36. A delicious mixture that stretches ham.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Dissolve jello in liquid and let set until slightly thickened. Whip cream until stiff (adding usual sugar and vanilla).
Then add jello and beat with cream until completely mixed.
Fold in remaining ingredients and place in refrigerator.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minute.
Remove any cubes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces. Cook according to directions on package. Drain. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish. Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg until thoroughly combined and evenly spread in pan.
Saute chuck, onion and pepper in oil until meat is browned.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese evenly over spaghetti. Top with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella on top. Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add celery, onion and sweet pickles.
Combine mayonnaise mixture to potatoes.
Toss lightly to coat potato mixture.
Carefully fold in the chopped eggs.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marisa's yummy meatballs
directions: Place all liquid ingredients in large pot.
Roll meat into tiny balls about 1-inch round.
After pouring chili sauce in pot, fill each jar with water and add to pot.
Cook on medium heat for close to 1 hour.
Serve with rice or as appetizers.
Great to cook ahead and freeze!

title: herb baked fish and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine hot bouillon, uncooked rice and seasonings.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with broccoli, 1/2 can French fried onions and the Parmesan cheese.
Place fish fillets diagonally down center of dish; sprinkle fish lightly with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Stir rice.
Top fish with Cheddar cheese and remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: savory baked brisket
directions: Trim visible fat from brisket.
In large reclosable plastic bag, combine remaining ingredients.
Add brisket and seal bag; refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican swiss steak*
directions: Mix flour and chili powder seasonings.
Coat steaks.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Brown steaks.
Add tomato sauce and salsa. Simmer over low heat, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or pasta.
Exchanges:
3 meats and 2 vegetables.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients and spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: mexican candy
directions: Boil together 3 cups sugar, 1 cup milk and 2 tablespoons white Karo.
Then in iron skillet, put remaining 1 cup sugar.
Heat, stirring until sugar is melted.
This is called caramelizing.
Add caramelized sugar to other mixture.
Cook until forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and beat until creamed. Drop on waxed paper.
If hardens before you get all dropped, add a little boiling water to it and stir until creamy.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Arrange peeled, sliced apples in greased baking dish.
Pour water over apples. Combine cinnamon and salt; sprinkle over apples. Cream oleo; add sugar, vanilla and flour, mix thoroughly and spread over apples.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: frozen cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and pineapple; let stand 30 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Stir marshmallows into cranberry mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan lined with plastic wrap.
Cover and freeze at least 8 hours.
Remove from pan.
Cut into 8 slices.

title: roasted red pepper spread
directions: Drain and rinse roasted red peppers; pat dry with paper toweling.
Place olive oil, parsley, lemon juice, capers, garlic and salt in a blender.
Whirl until capers and parsley are very finely chopped.
Add peppers; pulse with on-off motion until peppers are coarsely chopped, stopping several times to scrape down sides.
Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.

title: zesty baked hot dogs(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease tube or Bundt pan well with margarine or butter.
Cut biscuits into quarters and shake in 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon to coat.
Place layers in pan, sprinkling nuts throughout.
Combine last 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir until mixture starts to thicken and pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes. When cool, turn over onto serving dish.
For decoration, place nuts and cherries on top.

title: ham biscuits or party rolls
directions: Turn rolls out of pan.
Slit down the middle, all at one time. Add ham and cheese; put top back on rolls.
Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Cover with foil; let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Place in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chili and bean dip(appetizer dip-its)
directions: Pour all ingredients, except sour cream into an electric blender container.
Cover and blend.
Transfer mixture to a serving dish and stir in sour cream to taste, about 1/2 cup. Serve potato chips and corn chips as dippers.
Makes about 2 cups of dip.

title: fish bread for dogs
directions: Mix dry ingredients with moist ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use vegetable juice, beef broth, fish juice, etc. to make up liquid.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Heat beans and water to boiling; boil gently for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until beans are tender. (Add water if necessary.)
Remove bay leaf and ham bone.
Trim meat from bone; add to soup.
Season to taste.
Makes 7 servings (1 cup each).

title: one on one casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat quickly in 1/4 cup margarine or butter.
Push meat to one side and add mushrooms and sliced and chopped onions.
Cook until tender, but
not brown. Add broth.
Heat to boiling.
Blend yogurt with flour and stir into broth. Cook until thickened. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve
over hot rice.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth as directed on package.
Do not overcook rice.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder and mix lightly into rice, chicken, water chestnuts, mushrooms, pimentos and almonds.
Put into a casserole dish and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° until bubbly (30 plus minutes).

title: pork chop-potato bake
directions: Brown chops on medium high heat for 2-3 minutes on each side. Set aside.

title: vegetable dinner - cabbage scramble
directions: *Mix egg whites and Egg Beaters.
Pour into warm pan.
Cook over low heat until set.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
(Or if desired, use regular eggs.)

title: chili stacks
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Adds salt, chili powder, oregano, onion and tomato sauces.
Stir; simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer tortillas, sauce and cheese (ending with sauce and cheese) in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Cut into wedges.

title: one pot rigatoni
directions: Brown sausage meat in 5-quart ovenproof Dutch oven, breaking up meat with a spoon. Drain off all the drippings.
Add peppers and onion and cook until onion is tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasoning mix. Cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. lemon pepper and 1/2 tsp. garlic salt in the bottom of a pan.
Place cut chicken on top.
Pour soy sauce and water over top of chicken.
Add the potatoes and carrots.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lo-cal salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients but oil in blender. Blend and the slowly add oil. Blend until thoroughly combined.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone. Cut meat in cubes.
Cook macaroni in salt water.
Drain well.
Thicken broth with the flour.
Add chicken and macaroni to cheese and milk.
Put in a greased pan or casserole dish.
Brown cracker crumbs in skillet with butter. Spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chops with risotto
directions: About 1 hour before serving, trim fat from pork chops. Sprinkle pork chops with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook pork chops until well browned on both sides.
Remove pork chops to plate.

title: fresh strawberry cream pie
directions: Beat milk and lemon juice until thick.
Fold in whipped cream and chill in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups of strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Decorate with remaining strawberries and chill 1 hour or chill 1 hour and top with whipped cream.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Wash rice, add to puree and water.
Cut the pimento and onion into pieces and with the salt and oleo, add to rice, puree and water.
Boil together for 5 minutes.
Place in casserole and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Sprinkle cheese over top and brown.

title: kathy's brunch
directions: Break bread slices into a 9 x 13-inch pan after spraying with Pam.
Crumble cooked bacon over bread.
Pour Velveeta cheese chunks on top of bread and bacon.
Beat eggs, milk and salt together and pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook vegetables 5 minutes and then drain.
Put in pie plate.
Pour mixture of milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper over vegetables and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Use any vegetable you like.
Add mushrooms if you want.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix with mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 floured and greased loaf pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: mocha rum balls
directions: Dissolve coffee in rum and water in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix throughly.
Roll into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful of mixture for each.
Store in tightly covered container for several days.
Then roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Yields 4 dozen rum balls.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Peel carrots; slice thin and cook until tender in lightly salted water.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix, cover and refrigerate overnight, allowing to marinate.
(Blend ingredients into tomato soup and pour over carrots.)
Serve cold or as a vegetable salad.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown
meat.
Cook onion, celery and pepper
in
a
pan until transparent.
Mix all ingredients together,
saving
1/4 of noodles to sprinkle on top.
Place	in
buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter and smooth flour in it.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks, sugar, salt and corn.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° until firm.
Should take 45 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix sugar and melted butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar, & cool whip.
After mixing, pour over top of graham crackers.
Then spread blueberry filling on top.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: prize cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add flour; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: black forest cake
directions: Cream the
Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour, soda and cocoa.
Blend well. Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 1/4ths. In bowl, combine 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Coat biscuits with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place all pieces in greased angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Melt 1 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon water and 1 stick margarine and boil for 1 minute. Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in a little shortening.
Place the chili sauce and grape jelly in a boiler.
Bring sauce to a boil.
Add meatballs; simmer 1 hour or more.
Serve as hors d'oeuvres or serve over spaghetti, using the sauce as well.

title: pecan nut sticks
directions: With an electric mixer on medium speed, beat eggs well. Measure 1 tablespoon beaten egg and mix with milk; set aside.
To remaining beaten eggs, add sugar, flour, salt and pecans.
Stir with wooden spoon to combine.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Dip hands in reserved egg-milk mixture; use hands to spread dough in lightly greased 15 x 11 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread dough until smooth.
The dough is very stiff, but it can be spread out to cover entire sheet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and let stand until soft.
Add biscuit mix and sausage.
Mix by hand.
Shape into small balls and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in large bowl except spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Mix together.
Place in pan and pat into loaf.
Make tunnel in top of loaf and pour in cheese. Cover.
Then pour spaghetti sauce over entire meat loaf.
Place in oven for 1 hour.

title: banana split salad
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Set aside. In a saucepan, bring water to boil.
Remove from heat and add gelatin and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Toss bananas with lemon juice.
Fold bananas and pineapple into cooled gelatin.
Pour into 8-inch square dish. Chill until firm.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt margarine in microwave; add onions and green pepper. Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and celery salt; microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until tomatoes come to a boil.
Add rice, cheese and olives; stir well.
Microwave on 30% power for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
(It takes a little longer.)
Stir; garnish with green pepper.

title: cherry chiffon salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Eagle Brand milk, then mix in all of the other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: chewy cakes
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and eggs and beat.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 11 x 14-inch pan, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil for 5 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill for a couple of hours and serve.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients real good.
Store in refrigerator until firm, then shape into a log or ball. Roll in pecans to cover. Serve with crackers.

title: sunshine slush
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil in a large saucepan, stirring constantly until sugar melts.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in orange juice and lemonade.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pie filling and eggs together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cook remaining ingredients over low heat to melt chocolate chips.
Spread over cake while warm.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 10 servings.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Stir in sugar;
add shortening and beat well. Add
milk,
soda
and
baking powder;
beat
well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Add flour until
mixture is smooth and has consistency of cookie dough.
Roll out
dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out with a pie plate to
make
about
10 circles. Bake at 375° until each circle is light brown.
Cool and spread applesauce on each layer and on top.
Let
cake sit a while to absorb applesauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, soup and breadcrumbs together.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, mayonnaise, pinch of salt and celery pieces.
Place in covered dish overnight or for several hours. Just before serving, add the raisins and cashews.
Good with melon wedges and croissants!

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken, Ro-Tel, onions, bell peppers, garlic and bouillon cubes together in the pot. Cook until chicken is done; remove chicken from bone and return to pot. Add 2 cups of uncooked rice and 2 cans of chicken broth to pot. Cook on low heat until rice is tender.

title: extra-moist lemonade cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large mixing bowl.
Blend well, then beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.

Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan about 5 minutes, then thoroughly prick warm cake with cake tester or wooden pick through to bottom of cake.
Gradually spoon Lemon Glaze over cake until completely absorbed.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: mexican chicken corn chowder
directions: Cut chicken; brown with onion and garlic in butter.
Add broth and cumin and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cream, cheese, corn, chilies and hot pepper sauce.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Stir in tomato and garnish with cilantro.
Serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat at low speed.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spring cheese scallop
directions: Cook carrots in salted water; drain.
Stir flour into butter. Add milk gradually; cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Place 1/3 of the carrots in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/3 of the onions.
Repeat with layers of carrots and onions, reserving 1/3 of the onions for top. Pour cheese sauce over all.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: reducing soup
directions: Use a 2-gallon pot.
Mix all ingredients except squash and broccoli.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour or so.
Add squash and broccoli; simmer 15 minutes.

title: italian quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Remove pie crust from oven; reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Beat together the eggs and cottage cheese. Fold in the Mozzarella cheese, sausage and Parmesan cheese.
Turn into pastry shell and bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve immediately.

title: corn and cabbage stir-fry
directions: Melt margarine in frypan.
Stir in cabbage and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add drained corn, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: baked custard
directions: Put 3/4-inch deep hot water in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place in oven.
Preheat oven to 325° (165° Celsius).
Lightly beat egg in a medium bowl.
Blend in sugar or honey, vanilla and salt. Blend in milk or half and half.
Pour into 2 (6 ounce) custard cups or souffle pots.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Place cups in hot water bath in oven.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until a knife inserted just off center comes out clean.
A watery residue indicates overbaking.
Cool before serving.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in crust at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil one small potato; drain and peel.
Mash potato and mix with powdered sugar and oleo.
Add vanilla flavoring.
On wax paper, dump and roll out thin.
Spread with peanut butter, then roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill, then slice.
(A little Pam on your hands makes rolling up easier.)

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add flour, cake mix, salt and vanilla to the yeast mixture.
Mix well.
The dough will be sticky.
Let rise one hour or a bit longer.
Roll out and spread with cinnamon, sugar and melted butter.
Roll into rolls and slice.
Put into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with Powdered Sugar Frosting.

title: steve's marshnutters
directions: Place saltines on cookie sheet and spread a layer of peanut butter, then layer with miniature marshmallows.
Bake in 350° oven, just until marshmallows melt.
Optional ingredients to be layered:
coconut, chocolate chips, M&M's candies, pecans (crunched up) and peanuts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine butter and syrup.
Add salt, peanut butter and vanilla. Then add sugar, mix and knead until smooth.
Press into square pan lined with waxed paper.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: very ritzy italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip the chicken in the eggs.
Place the bread crumbs in a shallow bowl; coat the chicken with the crumbs. In a large skillet, heat the oil until moderately hot.
Place the chicken in the frying pan and brown lightly on both sides.
Remove from the pan and place in a baking dish.
Top each breast with a slice of cheese.
In a saucepan mix together the heavy cream, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture is hot and has thickened.
Pour over chicken and bake for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.
This is great served over pasta.
You can put the whole dish together and put it aside in the refrigerator for a day or two, then 30 minutes before ready to serve, bake it.

title: microwave sweet pickles
directions: In small bowl, combine salt, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, allspice, vinegar and sugar. Mix cucumbers and onions in microwave-safe bowl. Pour vinegar mixture over and cook, uncovered, on HIGH for 5 minutes. Stir well. Cook for 5 minutes more. Cool. Pour into a sterilized quart jar. Refrigerate.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Layer Twinkie thirds in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips, sugar and water in pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Mix egg whites and yolks with chocolate mixture in pan.
Then add Cool Whip and mix until smooth.
Layer 1/2 chocolate mixture on Twinkies followed by 1/2 Cool Whip and layer again.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil the potatoes in their jacket until done; peel and mash.
Add butter, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg. Combine beaten eggs; add milk.
Mix with potatoes until blended. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: mrs. bachman's dill pickles(ollie abraham)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Let stand to dissolve completely for several hours (this is important).
Pack pickles into jars with dill on top and bottom.
Pour cold brine over pickles and seal. Let stand on counter or in a warm place for 6 days.
Then place in a cool, dark place for 8 weeks.
Half recipe of brine is enough for 2 quarts (1 1/2 recipes will fill a gallon jug).

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain fruit well.
Add Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into cool pie shell.
Makes 2 pies. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Lay frozen bread out to thaw about 1 hour.
Cut dough in half. Grease work area with Crisco.
Work dough out in shape of a loaf. Sprinkle garlic salt, place 20 to 25 pieces of pepperoni, add pepper rings and sprinkle cheese.
Roll up and pinch together. Have fingers greased.
Pop in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and bread to meat and onion.
Shape in loaf.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Take out.
Make gravy and pour one can of beef bouillon over it.
Cook on one side for 30 minutes and turn and cook 30 minutes more.

title: dressing for green beans
directions: Melt Crisco in skillet.
Saute onions until tender.
Add green beans, vinegar, flour, sugar, salt, pepper and bacon.
Cook on low heat until it thickens and is hot.

title: broiled scallops
directions: If scallops are very large, halve them.
Place them into a colander or large strainer and rinse.
Do not let them soak.
Let scallops drain, then roll in towel to dry.
Melt the butter and mix in lemon juice, paprika and salt and pepper to taste.
Put butter mixture in a shallow bowl and bread crumbs in another.
Preheat broiler.
Dip scallops into the warm butter, then into the bread crumbs, until coated and arrange them in a single layer on a shallow flameproof dish.
Broil the scallops 5-inches from heat source for 2 minutes until brown.
Serve with lemon wedges for garnish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour half of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Let set until firm.
Make into large flat pancake on large round serving dish, then 30 minutes before serving, top with chili sauce.
Add flaked crabmeat to completely cover top.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Completely dissolve jello in water.
Add other ingredients. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan; chill until firm.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: To make the crust, unroll crescent rolls.
Arrange triangles in a circle on a 12-inch pizza pan coated with vegetable oil spray. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, cream of tartar, salt, baking soda and nutmeg; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Stir in eggs one at a time.
Add lemon, vanilla and almond extracts; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture and blend thoroughly.
Place in greased bowl and chill overnight.
Roll out on floured pastry cloth and cut with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: spinach salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: *Flavored vinegar adds a nice touch.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll out and cut.
Cover and let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except
ginger
ale)
together and then add ginger ale before serving.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables separately and drain well.
Heat undiluted soup and Cheez Whiz together. Blend vegetables into sauce and pour in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: brandy prime rib
directions: Using a sharp knife, make 1-inch deep slits evenly spaced over entire surface of roast and insert garlic slivers. Place in roasting pan. Brush outside of roast with soy sauce; sprinkle with pepper and let roast stand at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: carrot pineapple salad
directions: Mix boiling water with Jell-O.
Add cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple and carrot.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce.
Garnish with mayonnaise.
Contains 35 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: coconut nut pie
directions: Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: green punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Dissolve Kool-Aid in 2 quarts of water. Add sugar. Stir. Add pineapple juice. Chill. Before serving, add lime soda, ginger ale and sherbet. Serves 48.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon onto wax paper.
Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini, lemon and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon batter onto 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: fried zucchini blooms
directions: Pick squash blooms that don't produce fruit.
The male bloom. Wash under slow water faucet to prevent tearing of bloom.
Dip in egg and then in flour.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Very good.

title: amaretto cocoa mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store airtight.
Use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls to 6 ounces of hot water.

title: sweet 'n sour green beans
directions: Cook beans,
if
fresh	(or heat canned beans).
Drain. Keep hot.
Fry bacon and onion.	Pour off excess fat.
Stir in vinegar, sugar
and	water.	Bring
to
a boil.
Pour over hot beans. Garnish with onion slices.	Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn on grill
directions: Pull shucks back and clean corn.
Put shucks back over corn and tie.
Place in water for 15 minutes.
Put on grill for 20 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg and mix well. Stir in almond and vanilla extracts.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture and mix only enough to combine.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes until golden.

title: dump-it cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex well.
Dump applesauce in.
Dump pineapple next.
Spread dry cake mix.
Melt margarine or butter and pour on top of cake.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: fabulous cheese ball
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and dressing mix together and form into a ball.
Roll in combination of chili powder, then in crushed pecans.
Put in freezer and remove 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: tomato relish sauce
directions: Saute aspatita powder in olive oil.
Add pepper and 1 tablespoon tomato paste.
Add basil, clove powder, salt and brown sugar.
Let cook down for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add parsley, lemon juice and rest of the tomato paste.
Let simmer.
Should be pulpy.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve in cups.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large container, pour in bottle of Italian dressing.
Add soy sauce to color, approximately medium brown, and add garlic to taste.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop spoonfuls of dough into bowl of sugar.
Roll in sugar.
Put on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly with glass.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Take out when still white and puffy.
Let cool on pan a few minutes before removing.
Makes 4+ dozen.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apples in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
