Mix all ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes, until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits on floured board.
Peel and chop apples. In center of each biscuit place 1/2 cup apples, a small pat of margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pull end of each biscuit together to center and mash closed.
Place in deep baking dish. Meanwhile, bring water, sugar and margarine to a boil.
Pour this hot liquid around biscuits, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Serves 10.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream Nucoa and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and vinegar. Beat.
Add spices and raisins and beat well.
Fold in egg whites, slightly beaten.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut off crusts; cut each slice of bread in 6 sticks.
Bake sticks and crusts at 200° for 1 hour.
Roll crusts into crumbs. Heat peanut butter and oil until smooth.
Dip bread sticks in peanut butter mix, then roll in crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Let stand overnight or for at least 2 hours.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine peas and water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Turn off flame.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Do not drain.
Add ham bone, onion, salt, pepper and marjoram.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce flame and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove meat from bone and discard the bone.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Add to soup along with carrots and celery.
Cook, uncovered, simmering 30 to 40 minutes more.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, onion, green pepper and celery in large bowl. Bring to boil the vinegar, sugar and oil and pour over the kraut mixture. Let cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Set chicken stock aside; skim fat off.
Press one crust into deep dish pie pan, then put chicken and vegetables in the crust in layers; chicken first.
Then use chicken stock to mix with golden onion soup
(mix
cups
chicken stock with onion soup); pour
over
chicken and vegetables.
Take second crust and lay on top.
Pinch edges together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Check every 1/2 hour or so.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut meat 3/8-inch thick.
Combine all other ingredients. Marinate meat in mixture at least 12 hours.
Place in oven on top rack with bottom rack covered in foil underneath meat.
Bake at 140° for 6 to 8 hours.
Prop door open an inch or so to let steam escape.

title: cheese 'n sausage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shells until lightly brown, about 7 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a skillet, brown sausage until done.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onions and bell pepper until crisp-tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir sausage into mixture.
Divide sausage mixture between the pie shells. Sprinkle cheese on top.
In bowl, beat eggs until blended; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Slice and serve with tossed salad.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, salt and egg; mix well. Shape into meatballs and place in 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Combine brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir in flour and soy sauce; cook until thickened. Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, basting frequently.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in pan and bake at 425° for 1/2 hour. Turn oven down to 350° and bake until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine all but last 2 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Put in solution of vinegar and salt to keep from turning brown. Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well. Remove apples and rinse well. In large kettle, put apples; sprinkle with flour mixture. Stir carefully. Let stand for 30 minutes. Stir in lemon juice. Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens and registers 212° on a candy thermometer (takes about 2 minutes). Stir frequently to prevent sticking. Ladle hot filling into hot jars. Process in hot water bath for 25 minutes or pressure canner at 5 pounds pressure for 8 minutes. Makes 6 quarts. One quart filling makes 1 (8 or 9-inch) pie.

title: christmas tree date balls
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and eggs over low heat until heated through.
Add dates and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, cereal and pecans.
Mix until cool.
Shape into cones; roll in green sugar, powdered sugar or coconut.

title: ann's grapefruit biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar, baking soda and baking powder together.
Cut or rub in shortening until well blended.
Mix grapefruit juice and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, adding just enough to make dough soft and not sticky.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead a few strokes.
Pat to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into small biscuits.
Heat oven to 475° and bake 15 minutes. Serve with butter and orange marmalade.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: In skillet saute onion and celery until tender.
Meanwhile, cook cornbread mix according to directions on package.
When cornbread mix is done, crumble cornbread and add Kellogg's Croquettes, sauteed onion and celery mixture, cream of chicken and celery soups.
Mix well, adding milk or water until thoroughly mixed.
Put in large baking pan and bake in oven at 350° about 1 hour or until done.
Serve with turkey or chicken.

title: congealed salad
directions: Make jello by directions.
Add 1/4 cup pecans and pineapple and refrigerate overnight.
Whip the Cool Whip and cream cheese together and spread over gelatin mixture.
Cook pineapple juice, lemon juice, egg and cornstarch until thick.
Cool.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped pecans on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: beany beefburgers
directions: Combine ground beef, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties, 1/2-inch thick.
Place in a small skillet and cook on both sides until done.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine catsup, chili powder, beans, onion and green pepper in a small saucepan. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Place a beef patty on bottom half of each hamburger bun.
Top each patty with 3 to 4 tablespoons hot bean sauce.
Cover with bun tops.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler top. Blend in milk, corn syrup and eggs. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes. Chill. Stir in light cream and vanilla. Freeze in 3-quart ice cream freezer.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Form dough into balls; roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert(lo-cal)
directions: Fold in container of Cool Whip.
Top with cherries, drained.

title: smoked salmon frittata
directions: Boil 1-inch of water in a large skillet.
Add the asparagus and cook, uncovered, until tender-crisp.
Coat an ovenproof 8-inch skillet with cooking spray and place over medium-low heat until hot.
Add the olive oil and saute the onion until soft.
Add the asparagus and sun-dried tomatoes.
Add the smoked salmon and remove from heat.

title: minestra soup
directions: In a kettle, heat oil.
Add carrots, onion and celery and fry until just beginning to brown, stirring occasionally.
Pour in water and add bay leaf.
Season lightly.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and cauliflower.
Cook for 20 minutes longer or until potatoes are almost tender.
Add the garlic and parsley and simmer 10 more minutes.
Remove bay leaf and taste for seasoning.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese just before eating.

title: mound candy bars
directions: Mix together.
If sticky, refrigerate 30 minutes.
Shape into bite size balls.
Chill overnight.
Dip in melted chocolate chips (melt small amount of paraffin wax with chips).
Store in refrigerator.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix together by hand.
Add enough water to make dough.
Roll out and cut.
Cook 10 minutes in meat broth.

title: buster bar
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of butter and add to Oreo cookies that are in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat the cookies to make a crust.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour, then spread 1/2 gallon ice cream on the crust.
Put the nuts over ice cream.
Top with a cooked mixture of the powdered sugar, butter, chocolate chips and Carnation milk. Boil for 8 minutes and stir constantly.
Add the vanilla.
Cool well and then spread on top of ice cream and nuts.
Put in freezer.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Simmer mushrooms on stove or in microwave until tender.
In soup pot, cook onions in butter until soft, but not brown.
Add flour and blend.
Add chicken broth and broth from mushrooms and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, light cream and spices (to taste).
Heat to simmer, not boil.
Serves 10.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add milk, eggs and butter.
Add vanilla and chopped or whole pecans.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy chocolate freeze
directions: In small saucepan, combine milk and cocoa; bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add whipped topping and sugar substitute, stir to combine.
Pour into 5 ounce plastic cup; cover with foil and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer and chop into small pieces.
Place in food processor and process until light and frothy.
Serve immediately or re-freeze for future use.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Mix the shredded cabbage, green or red pepper and salt.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Drain off all liquid.
Pour hot salad dressing over the cabbage and mix well.
Serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onion with salt and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain off any liquid.
Combine all ingredients and chill well.

title: chicken or turkey a la king
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir mushrooms and green pepper in margarine 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream, broth and mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken or turkey.
Heat.

title: pot roast and gravy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; rub into roast.
Brown roast on all sides in hot oil.
Add water and next 6 ingredients.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or until tender.
Remove from pan, reserving liquid in pan. Remove bay leaves; skim fat.
Measure liquid; return to pan.
Add in 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons of flour and 2 tablespoons of water for each cup of liquid.
Stir well.
Stir flour mixture into liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Roll biscuits out with rolling pin. Place hot dogs and cheese on top of biscuits.
Roll biscuits up. Place on baking sheet, seam side down.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal delight
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cocoa and milk together.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Let continue until mixture forms a soft ball when a small amount is placed into a glass of cool water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Spoon out by teaspoons onto waxed paper and let cool.
Will harden within minutes.

title: capitol hill bean soup
directions: Add beans to boiling water.
Return to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and soak overnight in refrigerator.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water.
Drain.
Mix dressing, mayonnaise and water.
Layer potatoes and dressing.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, beating well.
Set aside.
Coat a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium heat.
Dip both sides of bread slices into egg mixture.
Cook slices 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Yields 2 servings.

title: caramels
directions: Cook, stirring constantly for 45 minutes or until a hard ball forms in cold water.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Sift flour with sugar and baking powder; add eggs, oil, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 4 minutes.
Spread 1/2 the batter in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread pie filling over batter, then top with remaining batter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Apple, peach, strawberry, blueberry or raisin pie filling may be substituted for cherry.)
Yields 16 servings.

title: steak and broccoli cheese gravy
directions: Cut cube
steak
in
small pieces. Flour each piece and brown in small amount of oil.
In a large baking dish, put can of soup, 2
cans of milk and flour.	(Put garlic salt on steak before putting in soup mixture.) Put steak in soup mixture and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef balls stroganoff
directions: Make beef balls in large bowl.
Lightly toss ground chuck with salt, pepper, steak sauce, crumbs and the egg until well combined. Using hands, gently shape the chuck mixture into 18 balls, each about 2 inches in diameter.
In 2 tablespoons hot butter in large skillet, brown beef balls well all over.
Reduce heat; cook gently about 10 minutes.
Remove beef balls.

title: logger stew
directions: Cover and cook over medium heat until done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Break up corn chips and place in bottom of a casserole dish.
Layer hamburger, sour cream, cheese slices and more broken corn chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, then enjoy!!

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine
coffee,
milk,
sugar and vanilla.
Stir well. Chill thoroughly.
Place	ice
cream
in	a large punch bowl. Pour coffee mixture over ice cream, stirring gently.
Top with dollops of whipped cream; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yields 1 1/4 gallons.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and orange juice together. Add oleo and pecans.
Form into small balls, then roll in coconut or sugar (powdered or granulated).
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 11 dozen (small).

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Take your oil and butter and heat slightly.
Add your sweet potatoes and your sugar.
Let fry until sugar begins to melt.
Do not stir yet and do not let burn.
Add 2 tablespoons of water and stir slightly.
Cover and fry until tender.
Add 1 drop vanilla flavoring (optional).

title: rice salad
directions: Put
rice
in colander and rinse with cold water.
Then mix all
of
the ingredients together in a large bowl.	Set in refrigerator for about one hour.

title: southern toasties
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese.
Add flour and work like pastry.
Divide the dough into 24 parts and press into tiny muffin tins.
Break pecans into each cup.
Beat with a fork the egg and brown sugar.
Pour into tins and place 1 whole pecan on top
of each one.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco salad for a group
directions: Fry hamburger fine.
Drain off grease.
Let cool. Break up lettuce, dice up onions, cut up tomatoes, grate up all the cheese and crunch up the Doritos. Add the taco seasoning.
Pour on the dressing.
Mix well and serve with hot steak from the grill.
Nice for family reunions.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter Pyrex dish.
Spread crushed pineapple in bottom of dish.
Top with a layer of pie filling.
Evenly distribute dry cake mix over pie filling.
Slice butter in thin slices and place over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° until pie filling is bubbly and cake top is slightly brown.

title: bishop cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Melt butter.
Add cocoa, then add dry ingredients.
While blending, add water.
Blend well.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend at low speed.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients.
Add to mixture with zucchini; blend well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding(diet dessert)
directions: Set out 4 custard cups.
Place 1/4 cup rice in each dish.
Add 1 tablespoon raisins, 1/4 egg, 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 packet diet sugar.
Sprinkle vanilla and lemon juice in each cup.
Stir and bake in oven 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Put half of meat mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with sauerkraut, then layer noodles.
Keep noodles away from edge of pan.
Cover with the rest of the meat mixture.
Mix the soups with 3/4 can of water. Spread evenly on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: In large saucepan, blend together browned ground chuck, onion, spaghetti sauce, water and mushrooms.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Simmer sausages in a little water in a separate covered pan until done. Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add to sauce and continue simmering sauce.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Put 1 cup of the sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half of the pasta, two cups Mozzarella cheese and all the Parmesan cheese.
Layer remaining sauce, pasta and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until done. Makes 6 servings.

title: jan metcalf's italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Place in covered container; refrigerate overnight, if desired.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Heat sauce (a can of mushrooms may be added, if desired).

title: sand tarts(sandbakkelse)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add egg and cardamom.
Mix well. Add flour and knead until smooth and firm.
Take small pieces and press into tins.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: chili bean soup
directions: Rinse, sort and soak beans overnight.
Drain and empty into a large pot; add boiling water, garlic salt, onion salt, thyme and marjoram.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 3 hours. Don't let beans boil dry; add hot water as needed.
Spoon out 3 cups of cooked beans to use another day in another way.
Mash remaining beans with their liquid.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Serves 5.

title: microwave buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine in buttered large mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes, rotating each 3 minutes. Stir.
Cook 5 minutes (covered).
Stir.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until it loses its shininess.
Add 2 cups pecan halves.
Beat until it can be dropped on greased cookie sheet.

title: tuna cakes with dill tartar sauce
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add celery and onion; saut until tender.
Remove from skillet and place in a medium bowl.
Add cream cheese and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add bread crumbs and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Divide mixture into 8 equal portions, shaping into a 2 1/2-inch cake.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Boil mixture of rhubarb and sugar 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O while hot.
Can in sterile jars.

title: hobo stew
directions: Add all together.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and then remove from pan.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and divide into 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop bacon in small pieces and saute until lightly brown. Chop mushroom stems; saute with peppers in butter.
Add pimentos; blend in seasoning.
Add cracker crumbs and bacon.
Let cool. Stuff mushrooms.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Wash tomatoes and cook whole until soft.
Mash through sieve. Mix all dry ingredients; add tomatoes.
Add liquid ingredients slowly stirring with whisk until blended.
Pour into jars, seal and hot water bath for 30 minutes.
Jars will seal.

title: cole slaw supreme
directions: In large bowl, combine slaw blend, apples, mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard.
Refrigerate; cover until flavors are blended (at least one hour).
Can use broccoli slaw blend instead of cabbage blend.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook elbow macaroni per directions; drain.
Chop corned beef and mix with all ingredients but bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork pineapple
directions: Select lean spareribs (2 1/2 to 3 pounds for 4 servings).
Cut strips between bones - one or two - rib pieces.
Broil until well done and golden brown.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar and oil; beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well again.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add all at once to the first mixture and beat well.
Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls and dip into granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets and flatten with either a fork or your thumb.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until it turns a golden brown.
Turn fire off; add butter and soda.

title: bearly hot chocolate snack mix
directions: Toss popcorn, marshmallows and graham snacks in large bowl. Sprinkle hot cocoa mix over popcorn mixture; toss to coat. Serve immediately or store in airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 week.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill a 4 1/2-quart pot half full of water, then cut kielbasa in half and then into 1 1/4-inch pieces and put into the pot with Old Bay seasoning.
Boil meat until it floats.
Add potatoes, cut to size you like.
When potatoes are nearly done, add corn and shrimp and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana-choco chip cake
directions: Cream butter with shortening and sugar.
Slowly add hot milk and beat until good spreading consistency.
Add vanilla; chill.

title: date nut bars
directions: Combine beaten eggs, honey and lemon rind; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then dates and nuts; mix well.
Turn into a greased, waxed paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out onto rack, remove waxed paper and cool.
Wrap in waxed paper; store in covered container 3 to 4 days (to ripen).
Cut into 1 x 3-inch bars; roll in powdered sugar.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Can boil 2 chicken breasts and layer in pan with dressing. Cook squash and onion in chicken broth.

title: campers cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add eggs, then flour and other ingredients, chips, oats and nuts last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef; drain and add to spaghetti sauce.
Set aside.
Mix cottage or Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg together.
Slice zucchini into round slices about 1/4-inch thick. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with sauce.
Layer half the zucchini slices on top of spaghetti sauce and sprinkle with flour. Spread with half of the cheese mixture, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until tender.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: better than carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and the 2 cups of bananas.
Spoon into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Spread frosting on top and sides and between layers.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of pecans.
(I use Cream Cheese Frosting.)

title: banana split delight cake
directions: Layer in bottom of large casserole dish;

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook and rinse noodles with cold water.
Cook beef with onions and mushrooms.
Mix with spaghetti sauce.
Layer with noodles and shredded Mozzarella cheese in 9 x 13-inch cake pan (start with sauce and end with cheese).
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and browned.

title: deluxe fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Mix far enough ahead of serving time so that the sweetness of the fruit will blend with the sour cream. This will not go watery. (Can be made the day before needed.) Serves 8.

title: sour cream dressing ireland
directions: Mash eggs and mix with dry ingredients until well blended. Add vinegar and sour cream gradually.
Wash and tear apart lettuce and put in bowl.
Pour dressing over and serve immediately.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan mix butter, cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese, stir until melted.
Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake about 25 minutes or until browned.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Press evenly over the bottom of ungreased spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Reduce temperature to 300°.

title: cut glass salad
directions: Mix each of first four boxes jello with water and chill until set
hard.
Mix
lemon
jello,
pineapple juice and cold water; chill
until
wobbly.
Mix Cool Whip and lemon mixture together and
beat.
Dice
all
jello into cubes and fold into Cool Whip mixture; chill.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: tortillas with chicken
directions: Cook 4 chicken breasts and cool; slice meat and place pieces in center of flour tortilla.
Chop chilies and add to 1 can of soup and pour over chicken.
Roll up tortillas and place in greased casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over top.
Let stand a few hours to soak in.
Sprinkle with lots of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Top with chopped ripe olives, if desired.

title: love cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Pour on top of cake batter; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for approximately 1 hour, or until set.
Cool well.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip; spread on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet pickle spears
directions: Drain pickle jar and pour boiling water to cover pickles that you have cut into spears.
Chill and leave overnight.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and pickling spices.
Boil for 5 minutes. Drain pickles and pour vinegar mix over pickles to cover.
Let set for 14 days.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and pudding thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Sprinkle coconut on top and refrigerate.

title: spanish delight
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and ground round until meat is brown. Add corn, mushrooms, chili powder and noodles.
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Shred cabbage and mix at a rate of 5 pounds to 3 1/2 tablespoons kosher salt. Pack tightly into crock, doing layer of cabbage and salt and mixing together after each layer. When layers are finished, cover with a cloth and weight down with a plate. Let ferment until bubbles stop (about 2 weeks at 65° to 70°). Heat to boiling and pack into jars and seal (2 pounds per quart).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pentch saled off, mix things you like in it.
Put it on the table, and you have your saled!

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breasts flat.
Fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika.
Use mixture to coat chicken pieces.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter for cake.
Add eggs, beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together lightly with fork.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(Cake may be baked in 8-inch layer pans.)
Cool.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Roll out 20 biscuits,
cut
in	strips, place on baking sheet and freeze overnight.
The	next morning, roll out the 5 Hungry Jack
biscuits
to	size
of a saucer, cut in half and bake.
When half
done, butter on both sides; bake until just brown.

title: pink stuff
directions: Drain pineapple; combine cherry pie filling, pineapple, walnuts and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend ingredients well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: meatballs
directions: Optional:
Add 2 patties (about 1/8 to 1/4 pound) sausage.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour milk over it.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, paprika, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Dip catfish in melted oleo or oil or spray with Pam, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange fish in well-greased dish or place on foil-lined cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine 5 minutes.
Add flour; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth, cream and sherry.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, nutmeg, pimento and olives; mix well.

title: jayne's fudge
directions: Place butter, sugar, evaporated milk and marshmallows in saucepan, mixing constantly.
(Use wooden spoon.)
Mix until it comes to a boil on medium heat.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Pour the bag of Nestle bits, vanilla and nuts (if desired) into the pan.
Mix, then pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cool in fridge.
Cut into square pieces.

title: creamed turkey
directions: Boil necks; separate meat from bones.
Gradually blend flour and milk over low heat in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over toast, rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: green watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: seashell noodle soup
directions: In large pot, boil potatoes until halfway tender. Add celery, tomato paste, pasta, tomatoes, onion, garlic and 4 cups of water. Simmer together for 20 minutes until tender and has thickened. Serve with crackers.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla slightly to mix.
Stir in the scalded milk.
Add this to the rice.
Stir well.
Pour in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Set this in a pan of water 1-inch deep.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm with cream.
Very good to take for a potluck lunch.

title: cheese-filled almond muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well, then set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix pumpkin, milk, butter and the 2 beaten eggs.
Stir pumpkin mixture into the dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add cinnamon, egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour.
Knead this mixture and spread thin on a cookie sheet.
Glaze with beaten egg white. Brush off excess egg white.
Spread with finely chopped nuts.
(Be generous with nuts.)
Bake in slow oven (325°), until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into sticks while warm.

title: rice and beans
directions: Boil water with rice and seasonings.
Cook pork in another pan, then add rice and pigeon beans.
Heat until done.

title: macaroni - cheese toss
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and cool.
Pour French dressing over macaroni and set aside.
Combine cheese, eggs and vegetables.
Blend mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese mixture. Add macaroni. Toss to mix. Chill.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Combine buttermilk and soda; stir until soda dissolves.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts.
Beat egg whites at room temperature with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Decorate cake with additional walnuts.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle with 1 can chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight and roll out thin like pie crust.
Cut in eighths and roll up, let rise and bake.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice in casserole dish.
Place cut up chicken pieces on rice.
Add water to canned soups; stir well.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle onion soup on top.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour, or until chicken is done, at 400°.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Boil beans, onion and salt pork until beans are just tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 2 crocks and bake.
Add water as needed so beans don't dry out on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°, then 3 to 4 hours at 350°.

title: homemade bread sticks
directions: Separate each individual biscuit and roll between hands to form a bread stick.
Dip each in melted butter and roll in topping of your choice.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dip in pizza sauce or Ranch dressing, if desired.

title: "the best" caramel popcorn
directions: Heat ingredients to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in very fast.
Pour over popcorn and bake in oven at 250° for approximately 1 hour.
Stir constantly to prevent burning.

title: lime pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in
1/4-inch
slices
and cover with lime and water.
Let stand
24 hours; rinse off well and cover with clear water.
Let
stand	4 hours; drain.
Heat cider vinegar, sugar, celery seed,
pickle
spice
and
salt, until lukewarm. Pour over pickles.
Let
stand
overnight.
Next morning bring pickles to a boil
and boil gently for 35 minutes.
Count time after boiling starts.
Add
food	coloring
while
boiling for appearance.
Pack in jars
while they are hot.
Cover with hot vinegar to seal.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add milk, butter and extract and mix well.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato and macaroni soup
directions: Wash and cut the potatoes into small cubes, bring them to a boil, and let them get soft.
While doing that, fix the macaroni to the package instructions.
If you are going to use an onion, you would slice it and put it in with the mixture.
Combine the potatoes and the macaroni, and pour the milk in and put the butter in.
Let stand for five minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage and separate leaves.
Mix hamburger, sausage, onion and Spanish rice.
Roll mix in leaves and put in a deep pot. Cover with the tomato juice and simmer for 2 hours on low heat. Salt the mix to taste.

title: caramel frosted pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beat for at least 2 minutes.
Then add other ingredients.
Beat well.
(The longer you beat the better, but don't overdo.)
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
You can use any flavoring.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with vegetable spray.
Mix hash browns (thawed), sour cream, soup and spices of choice.
Put mixture in pan; dot with butter and top with Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: grandma ellen hess' cold biscuit pie
directions: Warm apples and sweeten to taste.
Layer a dish with the apples, then add a layer of biscuits and another layer of apples and biscuits until all used, with apples on top.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place skinned, deboned chicken on bottom of the casserole dish.
Spread broccoli on top and layer with white American cheese.
Mix cream of chicken, mayo and lemon juice in a bowl. Spread on top of cheese, then add 2 slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cook Minute rice over stove.
Serve with rice.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Put yeast and sugar in warm water; let rise 10 minutes.
Mix flour, milk, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening.
Add yeast water.
Knead; shape rolls; put in greased pan.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: karhai chicken
directions: Add water, ginger, garlic, salt, peppercorns, cloves, cardamom, cinnamon, and cumin to chicken and boil until chicken pieces are tender and most of the water is dried up.

title: "light" strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in round cake pans (use "light" directions if desired).
Cool.
Slice each layer in two to make four layers.

title: 13 layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and add alternately with milk to the batter.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour 9-inch cake pans.
Pour 1/2 cup batter in each pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Cool on cake racks.

title: aunt chrissey's potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in chicken broth in a covered pan for half an hour or until tender.
Add cubed cheese and mash with a potato masher as for mashed potatoes.
Add soups and stir in parsley. Stir in pepper and evaporated milk.
Add enough milk to make desired thickness.
Heat thoroughly.
Can be frozen for about a week and reheated; heat slowly, stirring regularly to keep the milk from curdling.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Pour dry cake mix on top, spreading it out to make it even.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Layer coconut and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: paul bunyon sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll chilled dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Sprinkle tops of cookies with sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: churros(mexican crullers)
directions: In saucepan, bring water, sugar and salt to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in flour all at once and beat until smooth. Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth.
Spoon batter into pastry bag fitted with large star point.
Add lemon peel to deep fat and heat to 375°.
Fry churros, a few at a time, for 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown, turning as necessary.
Drain on paper toweling.
Roll in granulated sugar or powdered sugar.
Makes 24.

title: wayne's chili
directions: Mix beans, chili powder, tomato juice, onion and chili roll. Cook slowly until chili roll is melted.
Add ground beef (cooked slightly) and cook for 20 minutes.
Add more juice as needed to consistency desired.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add flour, vanilla and salt. Fold in pecans.
Roll into balls and press with a pecan in the center, or roll into 1-inch oval fingers.
Bake at 400°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: english trifle(also known as punch bowl cake)
directions: Mix Jell-O well in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add ice cream and strawberries.
Mix until thick, then add pecans.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on package.
Layer as follows: half Jell-O mixture, 2 bananas, half cake (crumbled), half pudding and half Cool Whip.
Then repeat layers the same.

title: dang good pie
directions: Stir together the sugar, pineapple, eggs, flour and coconut. Melt margarine; combine with other ingredients.
Pour filling into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°, until filling is set and brown.

title: bust your girdle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, butter, nuts and vanilla; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down with a fork.
Beat together cream cheese, 4x sugar, 2 eggs and pour over first set of ingredients in the pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Will be soft when comes out of the oven.

title: golden glow punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in concentrate.
Add apple juice and cold water.
Carefully pour in chilled ginger ale. Makes 25 (4-ounce) servings.

title: twinkie filling
directions: Mix flour with milk slowly and boil until thick.
Will look like paste.
Cool completely.
Beat until fluffy.
Add other ingredients, beating well as you add each one.
Spread between split layers of yellow cake.
Frost with fudge frosting.
Fills 9 x 13-inch layer or 2 round cakes.

title: cauliflower salad deluxe
directions: Place washed, torn lettuce in a large container with onions and cauliflower.
Add bacon.
Mix sugar with salad dressing and sour cream.
Pour over all ingredients.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Let set overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide in 4 or 5 rolls; wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator and use as desired.
Cut each roll into slices and bake in moderate oven until crisp.

title: chicken ranchero casserole
directions: Bake in casserole dish 9 x 13-inches.

title: pineapple peanut salad
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, lemon juice and salt until it thickens, stirring to prevent it from burning.
Add to whipped Dream Whip. Combine other ingredients and stir Dream Whip mixture into them. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apricot spice bars
directions: Finely chop apricots.
Cream butter, sugar and honey.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and apricots.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and brush with glaze.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: In bowl, combine egg, 1 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and milk; mix well. Add beef, pork and rice. Beat together with fork. Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water for 3 minutes or just until limp; drain. Heavy center vein may be slit about 2 1/2 inches.

Place 1/2 cup meat mixture on each leaf. Fold in sides and roll ends over meat. Place rolls in baking dish. Blend soup, sugar and lemon juice. Pour over cabbage rolls. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Baste once or twice with sauce.
Serves 6.

title: curry-glazed chicken
directions: Place margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and heat in oven until melted.
Stir in honey, mustard and curry powder.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Bake, turning after 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Do not cook!
Put into ice cream maker and let turn until thick.

title: amish fudge
directions: One cup sugar, one cup molasses, one-half cup butter, one tablespoon vinegar, pinch of soda.
Boil all together until done; pour in buttered pan and cut in squares.
When cold wrap in paraffin paper.

title: apple delight
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix and add apples and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: classic mac 'n cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute vegetables in margarine until tender. Reduce heat to low; add process cheese spread and milk, stirring until process cheese spread is melted. Stir in macaroni; spoon into 2-quart casserole. Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread as instructed on packets.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine until tender.
Add to cornbread. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° until it reaches the consistency you desire, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add flour and cocoa.
Gradually add milk, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cook until almost thick.
Put in almost done pie crust.
Beat together egg whites and 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar to make the meringue.
Put the meringue on top of the chocolate. Place in a 350° oven until brown.

title: snowball meltaways
directions: Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 1 hour at 250°.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Mix
first
ingredients together and boil 5 minutes, stirring
constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in package of lime
jello.
Let
stand
until
cold,
then fold in large can Carnation milk that has been chilled and whipped.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Makes 3 pies.

title: easy lemon cheesecake parfaits
directions: In a large bowl beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Fold in pie filling, lemon juice and rind. Add 10x sugar. Spoon into parfait glasses. Chill 2 hours or until set. Garnish with crumbled graham crackers. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fudge scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels with sweetened condensed milk in top of double boiler over hot water on medium heat.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture begins to thicken. Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Chill 1 hour until mixture thickens.
Line bottom of pie plate with foil.
If desired, place nut halves in bottom of plate, forming 2-inch wide ring.
Pour mixture over pecans (if used) to form a ring.
Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice.

title: chuck roast on the grill
directions: Brush mustard on both sides of a cheap cut of meat.
Place on heated grill and when done, meat will be tender and moist.
There will be no mustard taste.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add potatoes; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to potato mixture.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: german beer cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter and cream until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift cinnamon, allspice, cloves, flour, soda and salt together.
Dust walnuts and dates with a small amount of flour mixture.
Add remaining flour mixture alternately with the beer to creamed mixture; blend well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts and dates.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until tender; drain well.
Place layers of cabbage and corned beef in baking dish.
Blend flour, salt, mustard and 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add milk and water. Cook until thick.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter; add bread cubes. Stir until coated.
Place bread cubes on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Take a root of sassafras and steep in a pint of water and put in a bottle and when your husband comes in to quarrel, fill your mouth with it and hold until he goes away.

title: shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
In a large skillet, heat margarine over medium high heat.
Add shrimp and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently for 1 to 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in parsley and sherry.

title: hot cheese spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk, beef and sour cream.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Place in pie plate.
Sprinkle with pecans, which have been heated in the butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with Escort crackers.

title: quick tomato sauce
directions: Heat in a saucepan over low heat; blend in.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add gradually, stirring constantly.
Return to heat and bring rapidly to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients; pour into a greased loaf pan or lined muffin tin pan.
Bake until toothpick in center comes out clean or sides pull away from the edges.
Cool and serve.

title: lemon kiss cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter, sugar and lemon extract until light and fluffy.
Add flour and almonds.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Cover; refrigerate 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°. Shape tablespoon of dough around each candy Kiss, covering completely.
Roll in hands to form ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes, until edges are light brown.
Cool 1 minute.

title: garlic potatoes(microwave)
directions: Put potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup water over potatoes.
Pour melted butter with garlic over potatoes. Cover with waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Cook for 20 minutes on High.
Check to see if tender, continue cooking 5 minutes at a time until done to your liking.
May also be topped with cheese.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash for 5 minutes until tender, but not mushy.
Drain well.
Combine all other ingredients except oleo and stuffing mix. Mix oleo and stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with squash mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk and corn syrup in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until temperature reaches 238° on candy thermometer, or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when tested in very cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, do not stir.
Cool to lukewarm (110° on thermometer).
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Shape with a spoon into 2 1/2-inch circles, spreading pecans. Allow to remain undisturbed until the pralines are firm and sugared.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: arizona salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and store
in the refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken casserole delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight. Next day remove foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: You can also use the same amount of honey in place of the sugar.

title: pearl's pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix in flour, one cup at a time, until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven, set temperature at 300° and bake until lightly brown and toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: tailgate beef sandwiches
directions: Put beef in roasting pan.
Add dried soup mix then beef broth.
Cover and bake in oven for 7 hours at 275°.
Can also be placed in a crock-pot all day on low.
When done, shred with a fork.
Serve on rolls.
Serves 8 to 10.
Great for parties!

title: quiche
directions: Add any of the following or a combination: ham, Cheddar cheese, Swiss cheese, crab, onions, bell pepper, mushrooms, bacon or shrimp.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and blend.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Follow baking instructions on the box of cake mix.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix together until smooth.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with 1/2 of the sugar.
Cook with the slightly beaten egg yolks in double boiler until it thickens.
Add gelatine and cool.
Add the whites beaten with the remainder of the sugar, folding the whites in carefully.
Pour over the lemon meringue pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Keep in the refrigerator until served.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, water and Karo.
Cook until clear.
Take off heat.
Add 3 tablespoons jello.
Cool, then pour over berries in baked crust.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add jello; let cool.
Add strawberries; pour into pie shells.
Chill 2 hours. Top with whipped cream.

title: real texas chili
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook chorizo, beef, 1 cup onion and garlic until onion is soft. Spoon off excess fat. Add tomato sauce, red beans, refried beans and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir once or twice.

title: chocolate fudge delight
directions: Break the chocolate bars into small pieces in a large bowl. Add marshmallow cream, morsels and vanilla.
Put sugar, salt and milk in a heavy kettle; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and continue to boil for 10 minutes.
Pour at once over chocolate ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until smooth and all melted.
Add nuts (optional) and pour into well-buttered pan (1/2 sheet cake size would be the largest).
Cool before cutting.

title: beef and mozzarella cake
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef, basil, black pepper and garlic powder until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Add macaroni.
In 2-quart baking dish, spoon mixture. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican rice
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Add rice, onion, pepper and garlic.
Cook until rice is brown.
Add hot water, tomatoes, salt and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender, about 35 minutes. Makes 7 servings.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Smash egg, cake mix, coconut and butter into pan.
Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla until smooth and fluffy. Spread over cake mix.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon vanilla until smooth. Spread over cheesecake after it cools and refrigerate for 8 hours or more.

title: beef with green beans and sesame seed
directions: Cook sesame seed in a dry wok over medium heat, tossing until lightly browned and fragrant, about 3 minutes.
Remove to plate. In wok, heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil over high heat until hot, swirling to coat sides of pan.
Add green beans, onion and garlic. Stir-fry until crisp-tender, 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove to plate.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and seeds.
Add to liquids and blend.
Add dry ingredients must be moistened.
More buttermilk may be used if needed.
Mix in raisins.
Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: bubble solution
directions: Combine all ingredients; shake and let settle for four hours. Use only Joy and Karo brands.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water until fork-tender.
When cool, alternate layers of carrot slices, green pepper slices and onion rings.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat until completely blended.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate.
Can be prepared several days before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator for a long time.
Excellent.

title: pear marmalade(very - very good)
directions: Peel, core and grind pears.
Remove seed from oranges and lemon.
Grind them and then add pineapple.
To each pound of fruit, add 3/4 pound sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick enough that it does not run.
Put in hot jars and seal tight.

title: pork chop onion casserole
directions: Brown chops in lard or drippings.
Spread rice in oblong dish.
Reserve 1 Tbsp. seasoning from soup mix.
Sprinkle rest over rice.
Add hot water to liquid from mushrooms to make 3 cups and pour over rice.
Put chops on top.
Sprinkle with reserved seasoning.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until liquid evaporates.

title: chili
directions: Heat crock-pot to 325°.
Add meat; cook for 10 minutes.
Add onion, pepper, red pepper, brown sugar, garlic powder, salt and chili powder.
Cook for another 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans, tomato paste and tomatoes.
Turn temperature to low (or simmer) for 2 hours.

title: bow ties with veggies
directions: Lightly brown veggies in butter.
Add Italian dressing and simmer.
Prepare bow ties.
Serve veggies over bow ties.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.
Preparation time:
15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken in a single layer in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Press excess liquid from sauerkraut and spoon over chicken.
Arrange cheese slices over sauerkraut.
Pour dressing evenly over top.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: You will need a 6 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Place chicken in a long baking pan.
Slice potatoes over chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup in bowl with about 1 1/2 cans water.
Pour over chicken and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: alaska raspberry torte
directions: Line pan with graham cracker crust and chill.
Heat marshmallows and milk until smooth (use a double boiler).
Cool; fold in berries, nuts and whipped cream.
Pour into crust and chill several hours.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Melt margarine in 2 x 9-inch square baking pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Mix and press into pan for crust.

title: raisin molasses gems
directions: Beat Shortening with 1 cup Sugar until light and fluffy.
Add Molasses and Egg beating well.
In medium size bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to Molasses mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Shape into 1 inch ball, roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in upper third of preheated 350 oven for 10 - 12 minutes.
Cool then transfer to wire rack.

title: hot tomato aspic salad
directions: Buy the "whole" Ro-Tel. It is not as hot as the chopped.
Cut out small hard core of tomatoes before running in blender.
Onion juice is made by finely grating onion into a thin cloth and squeezing out the juice.
In spring you can use sweet Vidalia onions, just chopped.
They are not as strong and are delicious.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9-inch pans for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling, add gelatin and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and fruit juices.
Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and spoon in sherbet.

title: dad's italian meatballs and spaghetti
directions: In a large pot, empty contents of all tomatoes and tomato paste.
Add 1 large can of water.
Set heat on simmer.
Slice mushrooms and add to pot.
Chop garlic and add half to sauce. Save other half for meatballs.
Add pinch each of all seasonings to sauce.

title: panecuckendutch pancake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add and mix flour and milk.
Melt margarine in 8-inch cake/pie plate round.
Pour mixture into tin.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve immediately with syrup.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with shortening.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well, at least 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine milk and vanilla.

Add alternately with the dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Blend well after each addition. Melt German's sweet chocolate with water over hot water. Remove from heat. Blend in 2 Tbsp. cream. (This is the Chocolate Sauce.) Set aside. Pour 1/4 of batter into 10 inch tube pan, well greased on the bottom. Drizzle with Chocolate Sauce, alternating layers of batter and sauce to make three layers of sauce with batter on top. Bake at 350° for 70 to 80 minutes. Cool and frost with a chocolate glaze.

title: curried cheese appetizers
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, green onions, 1/2 cup olives and curry powder; stir until well blended.
Spread about 1 teaspoon of the mixture on each wafer; broil until cheese melts. Garnish with sliced olives.
Slice and serve.

title: yellow squash loaf
directions: Scrape and parboil squash about half done.
Drain in colander while preparing the following.
Fry sausage in skillet; drain off grease.
Saute onion in some of the grease.
Add chopped parsley and garlic; fry a little.
Add the squash, which has been chopped, and cooked sausage; let fry long enough to absorb the rest of the water.
Put into a bowl.
Add egg, salt and pepper to taste and enough cracker crumbs to hold mixture together.
Put into greased casserole.
Top with a few cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake until brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Sift baking soda and flour.
Stir into butter mixture until stiff batter is formed.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Blend in white chocolate and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder to buttermilk.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in egg whites (beaten).
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour cooked chicken and Veg-All in a pie shell.
Spread sour cream on top of that, then cover with cream of chicken soup. Shake a little Worcestershire on top.
Put other pie shell on top. Slash top a couple of times with knife and dot top of pie shell with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious recipes
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over cubed bread and add diced meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot punch
directions: Put in coffeepot; let get hot.
Serve.
You can add any other juice, like pineapple, or apple juice instead of cranapple.

title: noodles and cottage cheese
directions: Saute onion in butter until they begin to turn brown; set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions; do not overcook.
Drain.
Put noodles in bowl, add onions, cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix together.

title: microwave jello pinwheels
directions: Step 1:
Lightly spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Use a paper towel to spread on bottom and sides.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream potatoes until smooth, then add other ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn heat to 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond cookies
directions: Use stack pack plus 4 crackers.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place single layer of Club crackers on foil.
In heavy saucepan combine sugar and butter; heat until sugar melts. Pour over crackers.

title: english toffee
directions: Sprinkle nuts in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine; add sugars and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook to 300° or hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Pour over nuts in pan.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Place chocolate bars (in pieces) on toffee.
As heat melts them, spread the chocolate.
When completely cool, break into pieces.

title: joanne's bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except 3 cups white flour and wheat flour.
Let rise until bubbly.
Add wheat flour and enough white flour to make smooth stiff dough.
Make into loaves and let rise. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy sticky buns ii
directions: Thaw the frozen bread.
Cut each loaf into 12 pieces.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover bottom of pan with brown sugar; sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Take each piece of bread and pull out into rectangle.
Spread with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll up into a pinwheel.
With edge of knife, press "joint" of pinwheel down slightly.
Put a little butter or margarine on the top.

title: waffle whoopie pies
directions: Follow directions on box except for water.
Use only 3/4 cup of water.

title: chicken cheese tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Combine soups, chilies, and Velveeta in medium pan and beat on low. Cut up chicken and add to mixture. (Add juice from chicken also.)
Heat grease in a skillet and heat tortillas 20 to 30 seconds on each side or until soft.
Layer tortillas and chicken mixture in a medium casserole dish.
Begin and end with tortillas.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: it's a breeze cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Blend in chocolate chips.
Grease tube pan and pour in cake mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Grate potatoes; chop nuts and melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together; pour in melted butter.
Pour mixture in a flat oblong pan and bake one hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add all ingredients to hamburger, mixing well.
Let simmer until onion is very tender (approximately 20 to 30 minutes on medium heat, covered).
Stir often to avoid sticking.
Add 1/4 cup of water (or less) if mixture appears too dry.
For best results, cook mixture at least 6 hours in crock-pot on low setting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate - serve with favorite crackers.

title: tomato-mushroom bisque
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy, large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add celery, onion, leek, shallot and garlic. Cook 7 minutes.
Add 1/2 pound mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, chicken stock, wine, cream, lemon, thyme, bay leaf and saffron.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: more casserole
directions: Brown onions and hamburger meat.
Cook until meat browns. Have spaghetti cooked.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 2-quart dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Can be put in freezer to cook later.

title: crispy petite drumsticks
directions: Separate the wings at the joints.
Discard the tips.
Rub with salt and rinse clean.
Marinate the chicken in the sauce for 1 hour or overnight.
Dust the wings with cornstarch.
Deep fry at 375° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: finger paint
directions: Add a small amount of water to starch and flour to make a smooth paste.
Boil rest of water and add paste.
Cook until thick, adding a few drops of oil of wintergreen to keep paint from forming scum.
Add calcimine powder for coloring, mixing in small amounts until you have desired color.
Cool and store in jars. Makes about 3 pints (enough for 20 children).

title: stuffed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package. Drain and save liquid (use to make stuffing).
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/4 cup of broccoli juice.
Make stuffing according to directions (using juice from broccoli).
Layer in buttered casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan the broccoli, stuffing and soup. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered, for the first 1/2 hour.

title: no sugar mandarin salad
directions: Mix thawed Cool Whip.
Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Fold in with Cool Whip.
Drain oranges.
Cut into small pieces; add to Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Let cool.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.

Pound into both sides of meat. Brown meat in a small amount of Wesson oil. Remove browned meat from pan and cook onion until golden. Add water and tomato sauce. Stir until mixture thickens and boils. Return meat to pan. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday banana nut bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
Put in two loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together 3 eggs and box of brown sugar.
Make sure it is smooth, then add shortening.
Fold in flour a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Then pour in chocolate chips (also nuts if you like).
Bake in long 9 x 12-inch greased square pan for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
An excellent treat!

title: barbecue sauce(for 10 three lb.  chickens)
directions: Heat all ingredients together.
Dob on the chicken each time that you turn.
Keep the fire low.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and oleo.
Add slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, coconut and nuts.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
When cake is done and still hot, spread one 7 ounce jar marshmallow cream over top of cake.
When cake is cold, frost with chocolate frosting.
Keep cake in a cool place.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: party ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° until browned.
Serve warm.

title: fresh pear or apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with sugar/oil mixture.
Fold in remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into three buttered and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Icing recipe follows.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, bananas, sugar, lemon juice, pecans, sour cream and Cool Whip. Freeze.
Serve frozen or thaw.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Mix well with spoon; shape into bite-size sausage balls.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain, cool, peel and slice into bowl.
Combine cheese and butter or margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Stir until almost melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Fold into potatoes.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk with mixer.
Pour into dish with margarine.
Place fruit on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: miracle microwave fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup or more of nuts, if desired.
Pour onto buttered plate or waxed paper. Refrigerate to set.
Can be put in freezer, if you are in a hurry.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: easy chocolate truffles
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well. Refrigerate about 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in walnuts, cocoa or coconut. Store in refrigerator.

title: plantation bars
directions: Melt candy in a double boiler.
Add peanut butter and peanuts. Add Rice Krispies and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick nachos
directions: Lay tostitos in a single layer on cookie sheet. Spread each with layer of enchilada dip, picante dip, and cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts. Watch carefully to avoid burning chips. Have a cold drink nearby
when getting ready to eat. Good for a quick and easy snack.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine last 3 ingredients and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is beginning to brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, adding 7-Up last.
Mix and chill.

title: corn souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat 1/2 cup butter with 1/2 cup sugar until butter is melted.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Add eggs, baking powder and mix well.
Fold in corn.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: scones(modern version of scottish scones.  good for breakfast or tea.)
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Work in Crisco.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pat out dough on lightly floured board 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased sheet. Touch tops with water and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, sifted dry ingredients and milk.
Add extract, apples and nuts.
Grease pans.
Makes 1 large or two small loaves.
Before baking, put mixture of 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar on top of loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into an ungreased jellyroll pan to appear like all one crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until golden brown. Cool.
Mix the softened cream cheese, salad dressing and spices well.
Spread onto crust.
Then sprinkle finely diced or shredded vegetables on crust.
Peel skin from tomatoes and scoop out centers, using only outside and dice.
(Spread tomatoes on right before serving as they tend to weep.)
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese all over top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix soup.
Mix sour cream and spinach.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: blackberry flummery
directions: Wash and pick over berries.
In saucepan, combine berries, sugar, 1/2 cup water, salt and cinnamon; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until slightly syrupy.
Add 3 tablespoons water to cornstarch to make a paste.
Blend into hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and translucent. Serve cool with cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine the ingredients; shape into small balls.
Roll in flour or crumbs and fry in deep fat.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Place ingredients in casserole in order given.
Pour soup over top (undiluted).
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Combine Miracle Whip and sour cream.
Crumble and stir in the blue cheese.
Cut celery into sticks.
Put both in refrigerator. Chop onion and mince garlic.
Cook onion in oil over medium heat until soft, about 2 minutes.
Add the garlic and cook for one more minute.
Squeeze in the juice from the lemon.
Stir in tomato sauce, Tabasco and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove wing tips and cut wings in half at the joint.
Heat oil for deep frying to 375 degrees.
Cook wings in hot oil until brown, about 8 minutes.
Toss wings in tomato mixture.
Serve with chilled celery sticks and blue cheese dressing.

title: fettucini italiano
directions: Prepare fettucini according to directions.
Drain, gradually adding milk to salad dressing and garlic in small saucepan.
Heat thoroughly; remove from heat.
Blend in egg; add bacon, cheese and parsley.
Toss lightly.
Makes 5 servings.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter while cooking broccoli.
Drain broccoli well. Combine rice, onion, mushrooms, broccoli, soups and Cheez Whiz. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: chicken and corn soup with rivels
directions: *You can use pieces, but old hens have the best flavor.

title: gazpacho
directions: In food processor with metal blade in place, add onion to beaker; turn off and on rapidly, until finely chopped, about 5 seconds.
Transfer to large bowl.
Repeat with cucumbers, then green peppers, adding each to the onion.
Process 5 of the tomatoes until evenly chopped into small pieces; transfer to bowl. Process remaining tomato with garlic, tomato juice, olive oil and chili powder until smooth liquid.
Combine with chopped veggies in a covered container and chill.
Before serving, taste for salt; if too thick, add tomato juice.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with whisk 30 seconds. Add lemonade. Beat 30 seconds. (Mixture will be thick.) Immediately stir in Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Makes 8 servings.

title: mandarin veggies 'n' ham
directions: Put ham in a buttered baking dish.
Arrange bamboo shoots and water chestnuts over it evenly.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut a thin slice from top of peppers; remove seeds and wash. Cook peppers in boiling salt water, about 5 minutes; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Mix together hamburger, egg, salt, pepper, rice and tomato sauce; stuff into peppers.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix together and pour into shallow pan.
Strip with bacon and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Seve with a red cherry on top or whipped cream.

title: long island ice tea
directions: Mix together and serve over ice.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 c. warm water.
Combine milk, 1/4 c. water, shortening, honey, salt and wheat flour in a bowl. Mix in yeast mixture, and let rest for 15 minutes.
Add white flour, and mix until a dough forms a ball.
Knead dough by hand for 10 minutes.
Place dough in a buttered bowl, and turn to coat. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap.
Let dough rise for 45 minutes, or until it doubles in size.
Punch down the dough and divide in half.
Roll out each half and punch out the bubbles.
Form into loaves, and place in a buttered loaf pan.
Butter the tops of the dough and cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Let rise in a warm place until it doubles in size, about 30 minutes.
Place a small pan of water on the bottom shelf of the oven.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 25 - 35 minutes, or until tops are dark golden brown.
Butter crust while warm.
Let cool before slicing.
