Serve warm with your favorite jams and jellies or just plain butter.

title: impossible pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain hamburger and onion. Place in greased 10-inch pie plate.
In blender, combine the Bisquick, milk, salt, eggs and pepper.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese and 2 sliced tomatoes.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes longer.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix the cake mix together they way the box instructs you to. Bake the cake in a 9 x 13 dish. Once the cake has been cooked, remove it from the oven and let it cool. Once the cake has cooled completely, take a wooden spoon and place holes into the entire cake about one inch apart. Mix the instant vanilla pudding as instructed on the pudding box and very quickly pour the pudding onto the cake and make sure all of the holes have pudding in them. Mix the cool whip and lemonade together and then ice you cake with the cool whip mixture. Refrigerate your cake until time to serve. A very nice garnish for this cake is fresh sliced strawberries.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients and put in 1/2 cup of salt and let stand all night.
Grind onions, green peppers, red peppers and sugar together.
Put remaining ingredients in sack.
Boil 1/2 hour.
Put in jars.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans for about 3 hours or more.
Put all ingredients in 6-quart pressure cooker.
Mix well.
At 10 pound pressure, bring pressure up, then time it 1 hour.
Turn heat down about halfway to keep a steady pressure.
Let pressure drop on its own.

title: pepperoni salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onions, mushrooms and pepperoni together with dressing.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Toss lettuce and top with cheese.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Add to shortening mix with 1/4 cup milk and mashed bananas.
Mix until flour is damp and beat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add eggs and rest of milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in greased pans. Bake 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: fast n' easy barbecue
directions: Brown meat.
Add pepper and onion until tender.
Add enough catsup for desired consistency.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Cut lettuce
and
layer
in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Chop and
layer	other
vegetables.
Top
with Cheddar cheese. Place layer
of
lettuce	on
top.
Mix
mayonnaise, sugar and enough water
to
make
it
easy to spread.
Spread mayonnaise mixture on top of lettuce to seal.
Cover dish with Saran Wrap and chill. Will keep in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat on high speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to mixture.
Mix on low until just combined.
Stir in water until blended.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in cold water for 5 minutes (enough to cover raisins).
Mix rest of ingredients together until smooth.
Add raisins (drained).
Mix until smooth.
Put in greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix together at medium speed for 4 minutes.

title: sour lima bean salad
directions: Drain the lima beans thoroughly.
Add onion rings and celery. Combine sour cream, vinegar, sugar, horseradish, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Toss gently with the beans.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve cold.

title: chicken-fruit party salad
directions: Toss together the chicken, celery, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly. Arrange a mound in each lettuce cup.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar; mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool completely.
In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese and remaining 1 cup sugar until well blended. Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust. Refrigerate until chilled.
In a mixing bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add strawberries with their juice.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 12.

title: chicken and cashew stir-fry
directions: Blend together water, dry sherry, soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic and pepper; set aside.
Heat peanut oil in a wok or skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken, celery and onion.
Stir-fry 4 minutes, until chicken is cooked and celery and onion are tender. Add the mushrooms and cashews; stir-fry 1 minute.
Mix in soy mixture; cook and stir until sauce is thickened.
Serve immediately over a bed of cooked rice.

title: main dish spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, stir together undrained tomatoes, rice, sugar, garlic powder, 2/3 cup water and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 12 to 14 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir beans, beef and salsa into rice mixture; heat together.
Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the Imperial margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Add alternately and beat well the flour and 7-Up.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow to set in pan for about 10 minutes before turning onto cake platter. Cool, uncovered.

title: grape juice
directions: Mash the grapes.
Put in a crock.
Let stand.
Put 2 gallons of water to each gallon of grape juice.
Add 2 pounds of sugar; then put in a jug and let stand until it's done working.
Finally, cork tightly.

title: "hot bean dip"
directions: Combine ingredients in a glass bowl.
Heat in microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine all other ingredients. Shape into balls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: white bean steaks
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil until transparent. Add celery and cook until tender.
Meanwhile mash beans until some chunks still remain.
Add in onion mixture and all other ingredients except cheese.
Form into eight patties 1/2 inch thick. Place on a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with 1/2 ounce of Mozzarella on each pattie and bake for another 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugars and shortening. Mix until creamy. Add in the peanut butter and mix. Add in the eggs and mix. Add salt, flour and baking soda. Roll out into balls the size of walnut and press the center with a fork. Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: garden potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and Tabasco.
Blend these and then add to potato mixture.
Place in refrigerator for about 1 hour or until well chilled.

title: michael's salad
directions: Mix jello, cottage cheese and pineapple together.
Add Cool Whip.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of glass pie dish.
Spread can of chili over cream cheese and then sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Microwave for 5 minutes or until melted.
Serve with tortilla chips or favorite corn chips.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix 3/4 cup milk, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle 2 cups berries over. Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over berries.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° in glass or 375° in metal pan for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter; mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick test.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sauce for frozen meatballs
directions: Mix the 3 above ingredients together. Place desired amount of frozen meatballs in crock-pot. Pour mixed sauce over meatballs. Cover and heat until hot. The longer the sauce warms, the more flavorful it becomes.

title: micro brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt for 7 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and soda and microwave for 2 minutes.
Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Break in pieces when cool.

title: cinnamon twist pineapple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Turn pineapple pie filling into a 9-inch metal pie pan.
Place rolls around the edge.
Reserve the can of icing.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread rolls with the icing.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Let cool.
Make pudding while cake is baking.
When cake is cool, take a fork and poke holes in cake.
Then pour pineapple over cake.
Spread pudding over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: leftover casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except French fried onions. Bake in microwave on High for 7 1/2 minutes.
Rotate and cook for additional 7 1/2 minutes.
Top with can of French fried onion rings.
Heat in regular oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until onion rings brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Boil in large pot. As leaves soften, remove and cool.
Saute onion in margarine.

title: preschooler's butter
directions: Pour whipping cream into quart jar.
Close with tight-fitting lid (or container with tight lid).
Shake!
Shake!
Shake!
Soon you will have butter.
Spoon out onto dish.
Sprinkle with salt and mix.
Great on Club crackers or bread.

title: vinegar slaw
directions: Bring to boil the vinegar and sugar.
Set aside to cool. Grate cabbage, chop celery and onion.
Add salt, oil and barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Pour vinegar and sugar over mixture.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water; drain and mash.
Add ingredients except stuffing and butter.
Melt butter; mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 in bottom of casserole, holding back 1/2.
Put squash mixture, then remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sugarless apple bars
directions: Dissolve Sweet 'N Low in applesauce.
Blend all ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with a hand mixer well.
Refrigerate up to 1 week.
Makes about 2 cups.
A great dip for apple wedges, strawberries, or any of your favorite fresh or frozen fruits.

title: peanutty chicken and vegetables
directions: In deep skillet, heat oil over medium - high heat.
Add chicken, sprinkle with paprika and cook till well browned.
Remove chicken and drain most of the drippings from skillet.
Add vegetables to skillet and cook, stirring, till somewhat tender. Stir in peanut butter, chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste. Heat to boiling, stirring until smooth.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan and simmer a few minutes more until heated through.
Serve over hot, cooked rice and garnish with chopped peanuts, if desired.
Serves 4-5.

title: oh-so-good cornbread stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, cook sweet potatoes, onion and celery in hot margarine or butter for 5 to 7 minutes or until just tender. Spoon mixture into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in cilantro and ginger.
Add cornbread and walnuts; toss gently to coat.
Add enough chicken broth to moisten.
Use to stuff one 8 to 10 pound bird or place stuffing in a casserole.
Bake casserole, uncovered, in a 375° oven about 45 minutes or until heated through.
Makes about 10 servings.
Contains 413 calories, 24 g total fat (2 g saturated fat), 27 cholesterol, 476 mg sodium, 46 g carbohydrates, 3 g fiber and 8 g protein.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put eggs, bay leaves and peppers in a large jar. Cover with vinegar and water.
Cover and let set at least 1 week.
A favorite for Easter at our house.

title: melon trio with cilantro
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine lime juice, cilantro and honey in a small bowl; add to fruit mixture, tossing gently.
Cover mixture; chill for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings (serving size:
1 cup).

title: easy chicken primavera
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat 1 cup broth and garlic powder to boiling.
Stir in broccoli, carrots, pepper strips and onion. Reduce heat to medium.
Cover.

Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. In a cup, stir together cornstarch and remaining chicken broth until smooth. Stir into vegetable mixture. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Gently stir in chicken; heat through.
Serve over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Put sausage in large pot and render out.
Chop onions and celery fine and add to sausage.
Mix over low flame.
Chop green pepper and parsley fine and add to mixture.
Stir in poultry seasoning.
Add some margarine.
Moisten French bread and squeeze out excess water; add to mixture.
Keep stirring to moisten. Crumble in crackers; stir and add the remainder of margarine. Stir to moisten.
Remove from fire and add eggs; mix well, then add pecans and stir well.
Stuffs a 12 to 16 pound turkey.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix onions, mayonnaise, Swiss cheese and Tabasco.
Spread mixture into 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese evenly over mixture and sprinkle with paprika to taste.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fried squash or eggplant
directions: Peel and cut squash or eggplant into large strips (like large french fries).
Soak in 3 tablespoons salt water.
The longer you soak them, the better, but at least 15 minutes before frying.
Mix 1 egg, salt, pepper and sugar to taste; then mix well 1 cup biscuit mix and 1/2 cup milk.
Dip squash or eggplant in egg mixture; then into biscuit mix and deep fry.
Del-ici-ous.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Add nuts and bananas.
Pour half mixture into a jello mold.
Spread sour cream on top and pour remaining half of jello over it.
Let set for several hours.

title: spiced cabbage
directions: Fry bacon crisp and set aside.
Reserve grease.
In a large pan, cut up cabbage and onions.
Add water, bacon grease, garlic, salt and red pepper.
Mix well and cook over low heat until tender.
Add sausage.
Cook 15 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Bake at 350° until brown. Whatever starter is left, add the first three ingredients and start over.

title: grandmommy's bean salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and marinate in sugar, oil and vinegar mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: shirley's brown sugar chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to
Lightly
grease
or 2 cookie sheets.
Sift together
flour, baking soda and salt onto sheet of wax paper.
Beat
the
butter in a large bowl until smooth. Beat in brown
sugar
and granulated sugar until well blended. Beat in eggs and
vanilla
until
mixture
if fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture and the chocolate chips, combining well.
Drop 2 tablespoons of the
batter
for
each
cookie, 2-inches apart, onto cookie sheet.
Bake
at
for
10 minutes until set. Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack to cool.
If cookies get too hard to remove from sheet,
put
back
in
oven
for a few seconds to soften for removal.

title: seven layer salad
directions: First Layer:
Spread broken lettuce in pieces on bottom of 12-inch glass cake pan.

title: sun dill pickles
directions: Heat water, salt, and vinegar to a boil.
In a jar, combine cucumbers, dill weed, garlic and alum.
Poor hot brine over cucumbers.
Set in sun for 4 days, rotating 1/4 turn each day.

title: 24 hour macaroni fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine pineapple juice, sugar, eggs, flour and salt.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Mix fruit, marshmallows and macaroni.
Add whipped cream to cooked mixture.
Pour over fruit.
Mix well.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain, add water and cook until tender.
In separate pot, cook vegetables until fork tender. Puree in blender and add to beans.	Add milk, salt and peppers.

title: hidden valley ranch crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon and chill.
Garnish with bacon before serving.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound fillets until thin.
Lay out flat and sprinkle with parsley.
Top each fillet with a slice of cheese, then half slice of ham.
Roll up tightly.
Stir together mayonnaise and water in a shallow dish.
Roll each chicken fillet in the mayonnaise mixture, then in bread crumbs.

title: gram baker's potato salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick.
Cool and then pour over potatoes, hard-boiled eggs, onions and celery seed and mix well.

title: taco bean dip
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, blend together all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven or microwave on High for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: mother's potato salad
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Layer first with lettuce, then: celery, carrots, onions, green peppers, bacon (cooked), cheese (grated) and small frozen peas. Mix 2 cups mayonnaise with sugar to taste.
Spread over whole surface.
Sprinkle with hard-boiled egg or sliced and grated sharp cheese.
Make 12 to 24 hours ahead.

title: easy pie
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Mixture will be thin and slightly lumpy.
Pour into butter in pan. Sprinkle fruit evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: simple dill pickles
directions: Sterilize jars.
Fill with finely chopped cabbage.
Allow 1 teaspoon of salt and 1 teaspoon of sugar for each quart jar.
Fill with boiling water and seal immediately.
In a few weeks it will be ready for use.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs; cool and peel. Cut in half and remove yolks.
Place yolks and rest of ingredients in small bowl. Mix well. Fill halves with mixture.

title: home canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and stir the salad oil, onions, garlic cloves and green pepper for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling, then cook on medium-low, partly covered, for 2 hours. Fish out bay leaves, then can in heated jars and lids.
Yields 7 quarts.

title: nutty squares(this recipe is very good.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix oleo, sugar, flour, vanilla and egg yolk. Spread mixture onto a large greased cookie sheet until about 1/4-inch thick.
Moisten top of dough with unbeaten egg white. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs. Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Mix well. Add pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan(s).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: colorful chili dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: jean's sunday roast
directions: Put roast in flat Pyrex pan.
Salt and pepper and garlic salt both sides of roast.
Cover with foil and put in a preheated oven. Cook about 2 to 3 hours, depending on size or roast.
Then pour brown water gravy on roast and roast juices.
Mix, cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 teaspoons sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over all.
Chill.

title: no fuss egg custard pie
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Mix all ingredients well.
A blender works best.
Blend for 30 seconds. If not using a blender, beat eggs well, then add other ingredients.
Mix well; pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Pie is done if knife comes out clean when inserted.
Pie rises, but will fall and settle as it cools to form a light crust.
Very good.

title: chicken vesubio
directions: Roll chicken in the flour mixture of thyme, oregano, garlic and basil. Fry chicken and potatoes in butter. Saute onions, garlic, mushrooms and Chablis.
Reduce liquid, then add chicken and potatoes.
Add a touch of brown sauce, then simmer for a few minutes. Add Parmesan cheese.

title: olive dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: dutch oven breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage in frying pan; drain grease.
Line Dutch oven with foil and grease foil.
Line bottom of foil with 1/2 the bread pieces (remove crust if desired). Next, layer with 1/2 of the eggs (beaten).
Layer with 1/2 of sausage, onion and green pepper.
Layer with 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat all the layering, ending with the cheese.
Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: In bowl, combine chicken and fruit.
Arrange on lettuce-lined plate.
Mix yogurt and orange juice.
Drizzle over chicken mixture.
Garnish with sliced cantaloupe.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken b~b~q sauce
directions: Yep, that's it, only 3 ingredients.
Cook chicken on grill basting frequently with sauce.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese (one at a time), eggs (one at a time), 2 cups sugar and vanilla.

title: chicken parisian
directions: Season breasts with salt and pepper.
Put butter or margarine in a skillet or frying pan.
Brown chicken.
Arrange chicken, onions and mushrooms in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: basque potatoes
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in medium size skillet. Stir in parsley, pimento, salt, pepper, chicken broth and water. Remove from heat.
Reserve.
Pare potatoes and thinly slice. Layer slices in the broth in the skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover. Simmer about 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove potatoes with slotted spoon to heated serving dish.
Spoon remaining cooking liquid over potatoes.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and sugar in small amount of warm water so all is dissolved.
Add the rest of the water to make the 2 quarts needed.
Add pineapple juice and refrigerate this mixture until serving time.
When serving time is near, add the ginger ale. Serves 50.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together sugar and Miracle Whip.
Add hot water and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Spread 1/2 cup uncooked rice in a 2-quart casserole.
Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Lay a single layer over rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into a ball. Refrigerate.

title: apricot slush
directions: Mix together and freeze.
A 5-quart ice cream pail makes a good container.
Yields about 5 quarts.

title: quick and easy gelatin salad
directions: Put gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir until it is the consistency of a soft pudding.

title: oyster crackers tidbits
directions: Mix oil and seasonings, then add crackers.

title: green bean bake
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chef's salad-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut each tomato almost to stem end into 4 sections.
Mix remaining ingredients and fill tomatoes.
Arrange on serving platter and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cindy's taco soup
directions: Saut onions in oil. Add beef and stir until browned. Add seasonings and remaining ingredients. After soup begins to cook, simmer 2 hours. Stir occasionally. Serve with nacho chips, grated cheese and sour cream. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well; shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on unbuttered baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields approximately 6 dozen.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix the rest of the ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low for about 1 hour.
The longer it cooks, the better.

title: chicken kim
directions: Arrange chicken breasts on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover chicken with cheese.
Mix soup with water and spread over cheese. Combine herb stuffing with melted butter, mix with fork until stuffing is saturated with butter.
Spread on top of soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.
Remove cover last 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, cornstarch and salt.
Add well beaten eggs, syrups, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie shells.
Cook at 275° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.
Check occasionally to see that the mixture is not getting too firm.

title: 1-2-3 sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Remove garlic before serving.
Grill hamburgers a few minutes on each side, then baste with sauce.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups barbecue sauce.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, garlic, parsley and salt in a large zip-top plastic bag, shaking well to combine.
Combine lemon juice and oil; brush over both sides of chicken.
Place chicken in zip-top bag, one piece at a time, shaking to coat.
Remove chicken from bag and place in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough; roll into small balls.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Place in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Pour oil into an aluminum pan.
Wash and slice potatoes and place in a pan.
Mix in garlic powder, pepper and bread crumbs. Cover with aluminum foil.
Put on top shelf on gas grill (preheat on medium).
Cook until tender, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to boil; remove from heat.
Add flour; mix well and cool.
Add 1 egg at a time, beat well after each egg. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: hurry up cake
directions: Combine lemon cake mix and instant vanilla pudding.
Beat in oil, 7-Up and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well and pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, butter, and 1 cup chopped nuts together and put into a 9 X 13 greased and floured pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese, vanilla, coconut and a small amount of the powdered sugar. Spread over the first layer.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350 degree oven, sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts over top and continue baking for 30 more minutes. Sprinkle reserved powdered sugar over top as soon as removed from oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: steakburger deluxe
directions: Shape meat into 6 patties.
Place on heavy foil.
Season to taste.
Top each patty with 1 slice onion, green pepper and butter.
Arrange potatoes around patties.
Seal foil.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mama's chicken fantasy
directions: Dip cutlets in egg and then bread crumbs.
Saute in oil on medium heat 3 minutes one each side.
Place in baking dish.
Heat margarine and saute garlic, scallions, parsley and basil for 2 minutes.
Add thinly sliced mushrooms and continue to saute another 2 minutes.
Add broth and wine; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over cutlets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In double boiler, mix the water and cornstarch; cook until clear.
Put in bowl.
Add the jello.
Add the strawberries; stir together.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill; add whipped cream. May add sugar to jello and berries while mixing.

title: alexander's scallops
directions: Rinse scallops; saute scallops and onion in margarine and wine until scallops become white and fluffy looking.
Add mushrooms; sprinkle with parsley and pepper.
Add soup; pour in baking dish. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and cheese is melted.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and cool slightly.
Peel and cut potatoes into 3/4-inch cubes.

title: speedy swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in serving size portions. Moisten meat lightly with water. Sprinkle meat tenderizer on each side of meat.
Allow to stand 10 minutes. Heat oil in large skillet.

Sprinkle meat with flour. Add meat to hot oil and brown 2 to 3 minutes. Turn meat and add onions; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until tender and browned. Add all ingredients; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Serve as spread or heat and serve as dip.

title: caesar salad for two
directions: *Wash and dry.
Roll in paper towels and refrigerate.
Tear when ready to use.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Brown bacon; remove from pan. Add onion to grease and cook until tender. Add flour slowly until bubbly. Add vinegar and water slowly. Add all together. Stir until thick. Add sugar and bacon; cook 5 more minutes. Makes 1 quart.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Blanch peppers after tops and seeds are removed.
Cook beef and onions until browned.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until rice is tender.
Stuff peppers. Lay cheese on top and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat.
Mix in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Cook until boiling. Boil 1 minute.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
Add bacon crumbles. Cover and let stand.
Serve warm.

title: cheesy bread loaf
directions: Mix the margarine, garlic powder, mustard and onion together. Spread generously into bread loaf.
Place slices of cheese in bread loaf, side by side, lengthwise.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Put all ingredients together in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Stir and bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: tate's easy yeast rolls for a crowd
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 gallon lukewarm water.
Add to flour, sugar and salt and mix well.
Put in a warm place to rise for 1/2 hour.
Punch dough down with hands and make rolls into the size of an egg.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise to double in size.
Bake at 350° until rolls are golden brown.

title: pork chops delicious
directions: Brown chops; on each place a slice of onion and 1 teaspoon of rice (uncooked).
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water; cover. Cook over low heat about 1/2 hour.
Add tomato which has been fixed with green pepper.
Continue cooking until rice is tender, about 1/2 hour longer.
Sprinkle ginger on fresh pork.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain liquid from canned vegetables and mix all ingredients except crackers and butter together and put in 2-quart casserole dish (bowl or rectangle pan).
Crush crackers and spread them on top evenly.
Pour melted butter over all and put in the preheated oven.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes (or until crackers are golden brown) and serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle with mixture of corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except onion).
Pour into casserole dish and top with onion.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: steak marinade
directions: Instead of red wine vinegar, you may substitute other vinegars (cider, white or white wine).
You may also use any dry white wine.
Beer works well, too.
Prepared mustard or brown mustard may be used instead of Dijon mustard.
About 1/4 teaspoon each of basil, oregano and thyme may be substituted for the Italian seasoning.

title: high protein honey wheat bread
directions: Grease 2 (8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch) loaf pans generously. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups bread flour, salt and yeast; blend well.
In medium saucepan, heat water, honey, margarine and cottage cheese until very warm (120° or 130°).
Add warm liquid and eggs to flour mixture; beat until moistened.
Stir in whole wheat flour, oats and nuts, plus enough bread flour to form a soft dough.
On floured surface, knead dough about 10 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place until double in size, about an hour.

title: fresh apple cake with brown sugar icing
directions: Cream the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla .
Sift dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cake from pan and cool.
Ice with Brown Sugar Icing.

title: swedish potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and put into cold water.
Slice potatoes crosswise, being careful not to cut all the way through.
Roll cut potatoes in melted butter and set into well buttered baking pan that is large enough to hold them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden and tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with milk and cook until thick.
Beat egg yolks until stiff and add to mixture (save the egg whites for the meringue).
Cook about 1 minute longer.
Add butter and vanilla. Stir well.
Remove from heat and pour into a baked pie shell. Cover pie with meringue and bake at 350° until the tips of the meringue turn brown.
Let cool and serve.

title: barbara marie's tamale pie
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick and stiff, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Reserve 3/4 cup.
Line sides and bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole with mixture.

title: ranch garlic bread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine butter, dressing mix and garlic powder; beat until combined. Spread over cut sides of bread. Place on a baking sheet. Broil 4 to 6-inches from the heat for 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mustard short ribs
directions: Place beef ribs in shallow dish.
Mix mustard, sugar, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic.
Spread over beef.
Top with onions; cover and refrigerate, turning beef occasionally, for 24 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat 2 cups milk on simmer while mixing egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Mix well, add to milk, stir constantly.
When thick, add flavoring, coconut and margarine; cook until blended.
Place in cooked pie shell, add meringue, bake about 15 minutes at 375° or until meringue is browned to your liking.

title: eggnog
directions: Combine milk, water and vanilla.
Mix egg yolks and sugar; beat well.
Pour milk mixture over egg mixture; continue to beat. Pour into a heavy pot; bring to a boil.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sunflower yogurt parfait
directions: Scoop out frozen yogurt into 4 (1/2 cup) balls.
Roll balls in sunflower seeds.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.
To serve, place frozen yogurt balls in a serving dish and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons honey.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in flour.
Press evenly over bottom of a 12 or 14-inch pizza pan, forming ridge around edge.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend all artichokes together first in food processor, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with dill.

title: martha's squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except bread crumbs).
Pour mixture in a 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop cabbage, green pepper, tomatoes and onions.
Mix all together with canning salt and let stand for 2 days.
Drain.
Cook water and vinegar until it comes to a boil; add sugar and spice. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add cabbage, onions, peppers and tomatoes. Cook for 25 minutes slow.
Put in jars while still hot.
Seal with jar lids.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
In the hot coated skillet you just used to cook the hamburger, saute the garlic and onions.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Take the cooked noodles and place in casserole dish.
Add margarine and mix until melted.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix thoroughly.
Add meat, onions, mushrooms and garlic to noodles. Add spaghetti sauce and mix well.
Top with Mozzarella cheese (I use some Cheddar too).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with green salad and crusty Cuban bread.

title: my own spread
directions: Scoop out about 1/4 of the margarine and put it in the refrigerator.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to remaining butter or margarine.
Beat until brown and whippy.
It's great on toast!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layer of hamburger, sliced potatoes and onions in casserole.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Repeat.
Add the mushroom or celery soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare cake mix batter as directed on package. Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 13 inch pan. Cover bottom of pan with nuts and coconut. Pour batter over.

title: linda's potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put over top 1 cup crushed cornflakes or potato chips.
Bake at least 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cranberry citrus punch
directions: In a large kettle, combine all ingredients except ginger ale; simmer over medium heat about 15 minutes.
Remove spices.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and heat through.
Serve hot.
If desired, garnish with additional cinnamon sticks.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: Add cooking oil to frypan over medium to medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook approximately 3 minutes.
Add carrots, pea pods and meat. Stir-fry approximately 5 minutes. Add soy sauce. Let simmer for 5 minutes. Eat as is or with prepared rice. Serves 2.

title: 1 hour rolls
directions: Cream shortening, soda, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix yeast in buttermilk and mix altogether.
Add flour to make medium stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Dip in melted shortening and let rise one hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with apple slices.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: black skillet cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 10-inch black skillet or pan, melt oleo.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat buttermilk, eggs and melted oleo.
Add liquids to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn into hot skillet and bake for 25 minutes or until done.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and raisins.
Add to rice.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch with water.
Bring to boil 1 minute, until clear and thickened.
Add jello and a few drops of food coloring, if desired.
Fill baked pie crust with strawberries. Pour the mixture over the strawberries.
Chill for several hours. Serve with whipped topping.

title: fern's rocky road
directions: Melt white chocolate, pour over all.
Place mixture in paper-lined miniature muffin pans.
Melt milk chocolate.
Drizzle over each candy.
Stor in tightly-covered tin.

title: pistachio junk
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Decorate with nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: Heat oil in frypan.
Add meat, garlic and onions.
Stir rapidly until brown.
Add carrots, potatoes, tomatoes, water, lite salt, pepper and basil.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer at least 2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Makes 12 cups.

title: graham cracker choo choo snack
directions: Take 2 rectangle graham crackers and place vanilla icing between them.
Place graham crackers so long side of rectangle shape is at top and bottom.
Place glob of icing on top and place spiced gumdrops in icing.
Place glob of icing on bottom of graham cracker and place gummi wheel Life Saver into glob for wheels. Stand up for train.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour. Add egg, salt and vinegar. Add cold water; mix.
Roll out dough.

title: roast meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs with salt, pepper, thyme, nutmeg and cloves until well mixed.
Stir in milk, sour cream and bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes to permit bread crumbs to absorb moisture.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg, shortening and milk all at once.
Stir only until all ingredients are wet.
Pour into well-greased pie tin.
(I use a cast-iron frying pan that has been preheated in the oven.)
Bake at 375° to 400° until done.
Edges will be light brown and no sound of cooking will be heard within the cornbread.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes; do not microwave.
Can be frozen.
Place chicken in casserole dish; pat package of broccoli over chicken.
Pat cheese over both ingredients.
Add mushroom soup.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Pour melted oleo over entire casserole.
Bake until chicken is tender.

title: frothy orange drink
directions: Combine in blender and whip until slushy. Serve immediately.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Saute steak and onions in butter until meat is brown and onions are translucent.
Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into both sides of meat. Heat Wesson oil in a large heavy frypan.
Brown meat slowly, about 10 minutes, on each side.
Remove meat from frypan. Cook onions in oil until golden. Stir in remaining flour from dredging meat.
Add water and tomatoes; cook, stirring, until boiling. Return meat to frypan. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until very tender.
Serve on hot platter, pouring gravy over meat.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.
